title: potato salad for a crowd
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on until tender.
Cool slightly; remove skins.
Cube potatoes.
Combine dressing, salt and vinegar. Pour over warm potatoes.
Mix gently, then let stand until cold. Add remaining ingredients; mix gently.
Chill at least an hour (overnight is better), then serve.

title: browned turkey hash
directions: Mix ingredients in bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat 1/4 cup butter until it begins to brown (7-inch frypan).
Stir in paprika.
Quickly add turkey mixture and pack firmly on bottom and sides of pan.
Cover and reduce heat to medium.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes or until edges brown, adding more butter, if necessary. Turn out onto a heated plate.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Cook
eggs
in	simmering
water for 15 minutes.
Place eggs in	cold
water;
remove shells and pack into sterilized jars.
In a kettle, combine vinegar, sugar and spices.
Bring to a
boil; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour hot liquid over hard-cooked
eggs
and seal.
Store in refrigerator (use within a month; not for long term storage).

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid as directed.
Add Hawaiian Punch and pineapple juice.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Best if made day before.

title: pecan-coconut clusters
directions: Spread pecans on a large glass pizza plate or pie plate. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring at 2-minute intervals.
Set aside.
Place almond bark in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave at Medium (50% power) for 3 to 4 minutes or until melted.
Stir until smooth.
Cool 2 minutes. Stir in coconut and pecans.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool completely.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.

title: radican's tuna carbonara
directions: Cook pasta, according to package directions, in boiling water (salted).
Drain, rinse with cold water and drain again.

title: italian cheese ball
directions: Combine all and shape into a ball.
Roll in almond slivers (optional).
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with bread sticks or crackers.

title: date nut loaf candy
directions: Mix sugar and milk together.
Cook until a drop placed in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat and add dates and vanilla; beat until thickened.
Add nuts.
Place on damp cloth and roll in long roll.
Place in refrigerator.
When hardened, take out of cloth.
Cut into slices.

title: candy cakes
directions: Grease and flour a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Combine and beat eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla extract.
Add the sifted flour, baking powder and salt; mix well for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes in a preheated oven.
As soon as it's done, spread peanut butter on and cool.
Melt Hershey Bar in a double boiler and spread on top.

title: oat burgers
directions: Add seasonings and all ingredients except oatmeal to boiling water.
Gently stir in oatmeal until moist.
Let set until partially cool.
Make into burgers and place on nonstick cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well. Make sure the ketchup and eggs are mixed well to absorb the
loaf bread crumbs.
Pour into a meat loaf pan or large casserole dish.
After you have it in the dish, press it down, then put a cup of ketchup over the meat loaf.
Bake in a 400° oven for about 40 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Remove skin from chicken.
In large bowl, mix bread crumbs with next six ingredients.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture, pressing onto chicken.
Spray medium roasting pan (14 x 10-inch) with nonstick spray.
Place chicken in pan; spray chicken with spray.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown and juices run clear.
Serves 6.

title: artichoke leaf appetizer
directions: Blend cream cheese with remaining ingredients, except artichoke and shrimp.
It will resemble a paste.
Spread the paste onto each artichoke leaf and top with a shrimp.
Arrange leaves on a serving plate in concentric circles with the choke and heart as the centerpoint.

title: quick sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over beef.
Mix. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, then stir.
Turn oven to 350° and cook for about 1 hour, stirring often.

title: best-ever banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Add the melted butter.
Add the dry ingredients and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chicken-tortilla casserole
directions: Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips.
Mix soup with 1/4 soup can of water and chile salsa.
Spread small amount of soup mixture on bottom of Pyrex baking dish to prevent sticking.
Layer of tortilla strips, layer of chicken, sprinkle onions over chicken and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with layer of tortilla strips on top.

title: white sauce
directions: Heat margarine in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in baking mix, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly; remove from heat. Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Makes about 1 cup sauce.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Remove seed from chilies and spread flat in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with cheese.
In bowl, beat eggs, add milk and then blend in Bisquick.
Pour this mixture over cheese and chilies.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: cornish hens with mushroom stuffing
directions: Drain canned mushrooms.
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in a skillet.
Add mushrooms and saute until golden.
In a bowl combine parsley flakes, minced onion, salt, poultry seasoning and black pepper.
Stir in sauted mushrooms.
Rub cavities and skin of hens with salt and white pepper.
Lightly fill cavities with stuffing. Close with small skewers or toothpicks.
Fold wings back and under. Brush skin of each hen with the remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Place hens on rack in shallow baking pan.
Roast uncovered in oven at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: clam sauce for pasta
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add mushrooms, parsley and wine.
Add clams with juice just before serving.
Pour over spaghetti or vermicelli.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, sugar, salt and soda.
Add water, then oil and flour.
Add dates and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut off corn from cob, cutting down the cob twice and then scraping the cob with a sharp paring knife.
Set aside.
Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon and reserve drippings in skillet.

Add corn, margarine, sugar, salt and milk to skillet. Cook over medium heat about 20 to 25 minutes, stirring frequently. If corn is too thin, make a paste of 2 tablespoons cornstarch and about 1/4 cup milk.
Stir until smooth and add to skillet.
Stir into corn.

title: seafood cheese round
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire and garlic powder.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in onion.

title: potato salad and noodle salad sauce
directions: Place eggs, white vinegar, mustard and oil in frying pan, on medium heat, cook until mixture starts to thicken.
Let cool for about 5 minutes.
Add 7 to 8 tablespoons or more of mayonnaise; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fold in the potatoes or noodles.
Chill.

title: star spangled special
directions: Chill all ingredients and mix together.
I freeze large strawberries in ice cubes and float on top.

title: very good brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until smooth. Add eggs and blend. Add flour, cream and vanilla. Stir until well blended. Add nuts. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes according to how solid you want them.

title: * scotch shortbread *
directions: Mix and chill dough.
Roll out to 1/3 to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with hot tea.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy; add cream of tartar and vanilla. Gradually add 1 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Break up saltines and chop nuts.
Fold into egg whites.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes; let cool.

title: aunt edna's rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Flavor is best if allowed to mellow for several days before using.
(Put into jars with tight lids at room temperature.)
Makes about 30.

title: blueberry cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream the cheese.
Add other ingredients, except blueberries and nuts.
Mix with blender for 2 minutes.
Fold in drained blueberries and nuts.
Bake in Bundt pan for 45 minutes at 350°. Glaze with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: grandma's barbecue(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Add catsup, barbecue sauce, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, spices and onions, if desired.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: 3 step cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings.

title: date torte
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. Add egg and buttermilk and mix well. Add orange rind, nuts and dates. Combine soda, baking powder and flour. Add to mixture. Bake at 350° until done. Cover 1/2 cup of sugar with juice of orange.
Let stand until cake is baked, then pour over cake.

title: sour cream chicken breasts
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch pan, place dried beef on bottom.
Wrap bacon around skinned chicken.
Place on beef.
Mix together soup and sour cream.
Slice mushrooms on top of chicken.
Pour sauce on top.
Can be refrigerated overnight.
Bake at 275° for 3 hours.

title: pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown the chops. Remove and drain fat off.

title: peanut rounders
directions: Add and stir in margarine.
Blend in the powdered sugar.
Blend well and, as it begins to cool, drop by spoonful onto waxed paper.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no-boil tofu lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread spaghetti sauce on bottom of pan (generously).
Layer with noodles that have been dipped in bowl of water.
Spread with mashed tofu.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Top with more tomato sauce and continue until the pan is full, ending with sauce and Parmesan cheese.
(Be very generous with liquid, as noodles will absorb during baking.)

title: hurry-up cake
directions: Put in 8 or 9-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Delicious served with fresh or thawed frozen strawberries to use as strawberry shortcake.

title: cajun chicken strips
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first 6 ingredients. Add chicken, half at a time, and shake to coat. In a large skillet, cook chicken in butter for 8 to 10 minutes or until the juices run clear.
Garnish with parsley and peppers, if desired. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: date nut twists
directions: Take your favorite sweet roll recipe and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick.
Spread 1/2 of dough with this mixture.
While dough is rising, cook chopped dates, water and brown sugar over low heat for 10 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally.
Cool; add chopped nuts.
When mixture is spread on dough, cover over with the other half and cut in strips.
Twist and put on greased baking sheet and bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: grandma's broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter; saute onion.
Add flour and spices.
Blend in milk and broth.
Add vegetables and cook on low until thickened. This is very good using fresh vegetables (precook in microwave).

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in order given. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. Let cool slightly and ice with following icing.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix together with a fork, except apricot preserves.
Put 3/4 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread preserves over this and then the rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil. Brown ribs and drain. Pour mixture over ribs and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: dessert gingerbread
directions: Sift and measure flour, baking soda, salt and ginger; set aside.
Cream shortening until light and fluffy.
Add sugar and unbeaten egg.
Beat briskly.
Add molasses.
Add dry ingredients, beating until smooth.
Stir in boiling water.
Bake in greased and lightly floured loaf pan.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together the night before the sour cream, mayonnaise, caraway seed and dry salad mix.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Chop veggies and add to pasta, stir. Add seasonings and salad dressing.
Stir to coat; mix well. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Kiwi, strawberries, blueberries, bananas, orange slices, etc., may be used.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water until soft.
Add tuna, soup, onion, pepper and pimientos.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In large bowl mash bananas.
Mix in all other ingredients. Pour into a greased and floured bread pan.
Let stand 15 minutes. Place into a preheated 375° oven.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes.

title: strawberry tropical salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine gelatin, bananas, pineapple and strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 x 12-inch dish; congeal.
Spread yogurt on top of gelatin.
Cover with remaining gelatin; chill.

title: southern biscuit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 muffin cups (do not use liners).
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in milk just until flour mixture is moistened.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Add sliced water chestnuts and soup.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread onion rings evenly over broccoli mixture.
Bake 10 minutes more.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Sprinkle skinned tenderloin with salt, pepper and garlic. Place on heavy aluminum foil.
Mix the next three ingredients and pour over tenderloin.
Wrap tightly; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Be sure it has a medium, pink center.
For well-done, bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: zeppole
directions: Bring
all
ingredients
to
room
temperature.
Sift together the flour,
salt,	baking	powder and mace.
Beat the eggs with the sugar
until well blended.
Stir in the milk and combine with the
flour
mixture.
Beat vigorously until quite smooth.
Cover and let
stand
20 minutes.	Heat 2 to 3 inches of fat to 370° in
a deep fryer or a large kettle or until fat is hot enough to brown
a	1 inch cube of bread in one minute. Using a spoon
dipped in warm water slip a scant tablespoonful of dough, one at a
time, into the fat.
Fry Zeppole, a few at a
time, about
3 minutes or until golden.
Zeppole will turn themselves as they cook.
Remove with slotted spoon, drain on paper towel and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: thomas' dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar in separate container. Mix pudding and milk.
Place a saucer in bottom of flower pot and make a layer of each three times, cream cheese mixture, pudding and cookies.
Be sure to leave enough cookies to place on top to give the dirt effect.
You may add artificial flowers and gummy worms if desired.
Makes a good conversation piece.
Also may serve with shovel.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: spinach and broccoli(calorie counters)
directions: In covered saucepan, heat spinach, broccoli, water and salt to boiling, breaking vegetables apart.
Reduce heat; cook 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain; toss with lemon juice.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix in soup and chopped onion. Pour into baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Place Tater Tots on top in rows across cheese.
Heat for 30 minutes in a 450° preheated oven.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes until thick. Pour into pie crust.
Beat 2 egg whites until peaks form.
Add 2 tablespoons powdered sugar, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Spread over pie.

title: "gorp" trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; toss lightly.
Great in school lunches as substitute for chips!

title: creamy caramel pecan rolls
directions: For topping:
In a small bowl, stir 10x sugar and milk.

title: "no stomach ache later" dry beans or peas
directions: Season to taste.
Bacon or salt pork may be added during cooking or use cooking oil for reducing cholesterol.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift sugar and flour into large bowl. Combine butter, cocoa and water in pan and cook to boiling. Pur over sugar and flour and mix thoroughly.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and mix well.
It will be thin.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Prepare icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: delicious chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat 1/2-inch of salad oil in small skillet until very hot. Use 1 dozen tortillas from can.
Fry 1 at a time, 15 seconds on each side (do not let become crisp).
Drain.
In saucepan, heat cream with bouillon cubes to dissolve.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in huge bowl. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chili manana
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Pour off drippings.
Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt, pepper and chili powder. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes; set aside.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt. Add this to mixture alternating with buttermilk. Last add hot water with soda in it to cake mixture. Mix until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: quickee fruit salad
directions: Drain fruits real good; mix the Cool Whip and pudding until smooth.
Add drained fruits.
Chill.

title: crock-pot chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken for about 15 minutes. Add onion. Place chicken, tomatoes, vegetables and seasonings all together in crock-pot. Add vegetables and cook about 6 to 8 hours on slow to medium setting on crock-pot. Serve over white rice or pasta.

title: lemon lush recipe
directions: Combine the flour, butter and nuts.
Spread them in the bottom of a 9 x 13 pan and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Combine cream cheese (let the cream cheese warm up to room temperature), vanilla and powdered sugar.
Spread this in a layer over the crust.
Combine pudding, milk and 1 cup Cool Whip. Spread this as another layer over the cream cheese layer.
Spread the remaining Cool Whip on top (you should let the Cool Whip melt a little bit so it will spread easier).
Refrigerate.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine all but nuts in large frying pan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanuts.
Stir constantly until nuts become light brown.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda and spread thinly on greased shallow pan.

title: cool blackberry cheesecake
directions: Prepare cheesecake according to package directions.
Chill in refrigerator.
Mix gelatin, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add water; mix well cook over medium heat for 3 to 7 minutes or until thickened and clear, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Stir in blackberries.
Spoon over cheesecake.
Store in refrigerator. Yield 8 servings.

title: microwave one step lasagna
directions: Place meat in a 2-quart microproof bowl and cook (microwave) on High (max power) for 5 minutes, stirring once. Drain off liquid. Add spaghetti sauce, water and salt; mix well. Spread 1/3 of meat mixture into 11 x 7-inch microwave baking dish. Arrange half of uncooked noodles over sauce. Spread with 1 cup Ricotta cheese and sprinkle with Mozzarella. Repeat layers, ending with meat mixture. Top with Parmesan cheese. Double wrap with plastic wrap. Place dish on microwave rack if possible and cook (microwave) on 50 (simmer) for 30 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella. Leave uncovered and cook (microwave) on 50 (simmer) about 2 minutes or until cheese is melted. Sprinkle with parsley, if desired, and serve with additional Parmesan, if desired. Serve with garlic bread for a tasty treat!

title: italian dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar and seasonings.
Mix well.
In a saucepan, heat milk, water and butter until warm (butter does not need to melt).
Add to flour mixture. Stir in egg.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in Parmesan cheese and enough remaining flour to make a firm dough. Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Let rise in a warm oven 15 minutes, covered.
Punch down and divide into 16 pieces.
Form into balls and dip into melted butter.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and let rise in warm oven 10 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl; mix well.
Roll out and cut to desired size.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: summer lasagna
directions: Combine tomato sauce, onion, basil, salt, pepper and oregano in a small mixing bowl; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and parsley; set aside.
Peel zucchini and cut off ends.
Slice zucchini lengthwise into strips.
Arrange strips in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at High for 6 to 8 minutes, or until fork-tender, rearranging after half the time.
Drain liquid; place zucchini on paper towels to absorb excess moisture.
Cool slightly.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook the first five ingredients until thick.
Add peanut butter and stir.
Pour into pie crust, icing with the egg whites.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add the next 3 ingredients; simmer for 15 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer:
1/3 hamburger mixture, 6 tortillas and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Repeat for second layer.
Put remaining meat sauce on top.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 375° oven, covered. Serve with taco sauce, chopped tomatoes and shredded lettuce.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut and dip top in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet, sugar side up.
Bake at 375°
for 8
minutes.
These cookies are very good.
Don't overbake.	Don't freeze.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Heat a sprayed wok or large skillet (nonstick spray).
Add broccoli, peppers, zucchini, squash and garlic.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and peas and saute for 2 minutes more. Place parsley, basil leaves and chicken bouillon in a food processor fitted with the metal blade and process until parsley is finely chopped.

title: cream cheese salad
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle dry jello into mixture (your choice of flavor).
May add nuts or cherries.

title: spinach balls
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients except stuffing mix.
When well blended, stir in stuffing mix and let stand 20 minutes while mixture firms slightly.
Shape into rounded teaspoon and arrange on ungreased cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 20 minutes, until hot and slightly browned.
May be cooled, wrapped and frozen.
Just reheat on a baking sheet 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 112 balls.
Contains 55 calories for 2 balls.

title: picante dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and picante sauce thoroughly. Top with layer of Cheddar cheese, followed by tomatoes and then green onions.

title: white mountain cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Cut cake in slices.

Combine cream cheese and confectioners sugar. Spread 1/2 of whipped topping. Arrange 1/2 cake slices on top of Cool Whip. Press lightly. Spread with cream cheese mixture. Put remaining cake slices over that and spread remaining Cool Whip. Put cherries on top.
Fridge for 2 hours.

title: easy parmesan cream sauce
directions: In a medium size saucepan, heat the chicken broth to a boil. Reduce the heat to low and stir in the country gravy mix, Parmesan, and dill weed.
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Thin with Zinfandel, if desired. If you do not want to use the wine, use additional broth.
This is very good with chicken.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat through.
Serve over cooked egg noodles.

title: mother's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Gradually blend in dry ingredients.
Chill the dough at least 3 hours.
Roll 1/8 to 1/4-inch thickness on a lightly floured pastry sheet.
Cut cookies with floured cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: spicy franks
directions: Combine jelly and mustard in 1-1/2 quart glass casserole. Microwave for about 4 minutes on ROAST, or until jelly melts. Beat well with rotary beater to blend in mustard.
Cut each frank cross-wise into 6 pieces.
Stir into jelly mixture and continue cooking 3 to 4 minutes on HIGH, or until franks are hot.
Serve in chafing dish with tooth- picks.
About 60 appetizers.

title: beef roast
directions: Roll roast in flour. Brown in vegetable oil in Dutch oven. Stir in apple juice, celery and onion soup mix. Cook over medium heat until tender. Add sliced apples and simmer 7 to 10 minutes. Place roast on platter and gravy in bowl to ladle over vegetables.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken with 1 teaspoon salt and 3 bay leaves until tender.
Cool, bone and dice.
Combine all other ingredients; refrigerate.
Banana or pineapple may be substituted for chestnuts or pecans.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except eggs.
Mix well, then stir in beaten eggs.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine fat, salt and peanut butter and mix well.
Gradually add granulated sugar and brown sugar.
Cream thoroughly after each addition.
Add eggs and milk, mixing well.
Sift together the flour and soda.
Blend with first mixture.
Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Or roll the dough into balls 3/4 to 1 inch in diameter.
Place on baking sheets; press lightly with a fork to flatten.
Bake at 325° (slow oven) 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dozen cookies.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook until thickened and smooth.
Stir in cheese.
Cook over low heat, stirring until cheese melts.

title: corn cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix meal, eggs, oil and corn.
Fold in sour cream and mix well.
Pour into a greased, preheated skillet. Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, saving juice.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add brown sugar and small amount of pineapple juice to form syrup to cover bottom of pan.
Add pineapple and spread out. Prepare cake mix according to box directions.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water.
Add flavoring and salt.
Pour slowly over corn.
Stir with spoon, as that all will be evenly coated.
Make same size popcorn balls.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour into two unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brownies for a crowd
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 pan with Baker's Joy. In large mixing bowl, mix butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Fold in nuts. Pour into pan. Place pan on baking sheet (this protects bottom from overbaking while top bakes). Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Cool, then freeze for 1 hour before cutting. These brownies can be frozen and used for lunches.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place rhubarb in ungreased pan (10 x 6-inch).
Sprinkle with salt.
Measure sugar, flour and cinnamon into bowl.
Add margarine and mix thoroughly until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over the rhubarb.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until topping is golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: cheese grits souffle
directions: Cook grits in water with salt until done, but not stiff.
Add butter and cheese and set aside to let them melt.
Fold in beaten eggs.
Pour into 1-quart buttered casserole.
Cover with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: ward's green salad
directions: Place all ingredients in large bowl and toss.
Serve with vinegar and oil dressing.
The shredding and dicing makes a big difference.

title: no added fat corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. For the margarine, I use nonfat.
Some people do not like the taste of nonfat and use low-fat.

title: layered pudding dessert
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts, press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 10x sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip together and spread this on the cooled crust.
Mix vanilla pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk together and spread this on cream cheese layer.
Mix chocolate pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk together and spread this on vanilla pudding layer.
Spread 2 cups Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: wagon wheels
directions: Mix together shortening and sugar.
Stir in molasses and water.
Sift together remaining ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Chill dough several hours or overnight.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch circles.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: In a large saucepot, add all ingredients. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat; simmer until vegetables and rice are tender, about 20 minutes. Remove bay leaf and serve. Makes 7 cups. Need anything be said on how good it is on the second or third day!

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; let cool.
Add pineapple (including juice), mashed bananas and thawed strawberries.
Put 1/2 Jell-O mixture in dish; let congeal. After this has congealed, cover with layer of sour cream.
Put remaining Jell-O mixture on top of this.
Return to refrigerator to set.

title: sweet potato pie(kids recipe #3)
directions: Drain yams and mash until smooth.
Add milk and eggs and beat until well mixed.
Add the honey, salt, ginger, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg.
Mix well with spoon.
Line your greased pie pan with pastry shell and trim extra crust.
Pour mixture into the pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Stir together and cook until thick and makes a ball.
Pour onto wax paper.
Knead with food color (15 drops) until smooth.
Store in sealed plastic container.

title: chicken-in-rice
directions: Turn oven to 350°. Put 2 tablespoons margarine in 9 1/2 x 11-inch glass dish to melt. Dump rice in dish. Cook chicken 2 minutes in microwave, then turn. Cook total of 6 minutes or until looks done. Set aside to let cool. Mix soup and add 1/2 can milk and 1/2 can water; stir. Add chopped onions, salt and pepper. When chicken cools, tear into pieces and lay on rice. Pour soup mixture over chicken and rice. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. Stir after 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Bake chicken in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is done. Cook noodles as directed on bag. Cube the cheese in 4-inch cubes. Drain noodles but leave 1 1/2 cups of the water from the noodles in the pan with the noodles. Add the diced cheese to the noodles. Stir the cheese and noodles until the cheese is melted. Cook the broccoli until done, then drain. Cut the chicken into cubes. Mix all of it together.

title: golden apple bundles
directions: In a bowl, combine apples, nuts, brown sugar, raisins, flour and cinnamon; set aside.
Roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness; cut into 5-inch circles.
Spoon about 1/4 cup apple mixture into center of each circle.
Moisten edges of pastry with water; fold over and seal with a fork.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400°; bake 10 minutes longer.
Brush each with milk; sprinkle with sugar.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: cheddar baked potato slices
directions: Combine soup, paprika and pepper.
Layer potatoes and onion, overlapping rows.
Sprinkle cheese and pour soup mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Uncover for 10 minutes.

title: low-fat vegetable lasagna
directions: Cover bottom of baking dish with sauce.
Put layer of uncooked noodles (about 3).
Combine cottage cheese, Cheddar, parsley, Egg Beaters, basil and garlic.
Add a layer of mixture, slice a layer of zucchini, noodles, cheese mixture, zucchini, until dish is full.
Pour rest of sauce over ingredients, rinse can and add to dish.
Add enough water to bring liquid to 3/4 of pan. Cover with foil and bake at 450° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and melt. Serve.

title: bambino huey
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and the butter. Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Mix 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar. (Reserve some of the powdered sugar to sprinkle on top.) Pour second mixture into baking pan as second layer. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle with reserved powdered sugar and serve warm with whipped topping.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and lemon juice, stirring constantly until clear.
Add dry jello and stir well.
Cool.
Add strawberries.
Fill one 10-inch baked pie shell.

title: mary lou's hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 3 hours.

title: slaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and turmeric to a boil for 1 minute. Pour over cabbage, pepper and onion.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Crumble yeast into large mixing bowl; add sugar, salt and water.
Add well beaten egg.
Sift flour once before measuring. Add one-half of flour and beat well.
Add melted shortening and mix in remainder of flour.
Punch down; cover tightly and place in refrigerator.
Rolls are much better second and third days than on first day.
Dough also works much easier if thoroughly chilled before using.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: dinner rolls
directions: In cup, dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Cream Crisco, sugar and 1 1/4 teaspoons salt in large bowl.
Add yeast mixture to bowl.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Sift flour (3 cups at a time) and mix with wire whisk.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: old-fashion egg custard
directions: Combine the dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and add to dry mixture and beat well.
Add milk gradually, then the melted butter.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until done.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine the ground zucchini, peppers and onions.
Add salt and let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain and rinse with cold water.
Let stand to drain while mixing together in a large cooking kettle the sugar, vinegar, spices and cornstarch.
Mix well, then add zucchini, peppers and onions.
Cook for 1/2 hour, stirring the mixture every so often.
Put into hot jars and seal. This amount makes about 6 pints.

title: kentucky fried chicken
directions: Put in plastic bag; mix well.
Add chicken; coat well.
(Best to coat one or two pieces at a time.)
Lay out until coating is moist.
Re-coat chicken.
Melt 1/4 pound margarine in large baking dish; add chicken.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until tender.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream together margarine and sugar, add cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Stir in syrup.
Add eggs, one at a time, stirring after each addition until blended, stir in rolled oats into mixture.
Pour into pie shell and bake for about one hour or until knife inserted into center of pie comes out clean.

title: rice parisian
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 1-quart baking dish; cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix together and spread on No Sugar Carrot Cake.

title: hash brown scallop potatoes
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and garlic salt. Add onions, potatoes and Cheddar cheese; mix well. Pour into a 10 x 13 baking dish. Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: perfect cornbread
directions: Mix only a little.
Bake in pan with a little vegetable oil in bottom.
Cook for 20 minutes at 400° or when brown on top.

title: chocolate pastry cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla and cool to room temperature.
Combine pie crust mix and 3/4 cup chocolate mixture in a small bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer until smooth.
Divide pastry in 6 equal portions.
Press each portion onto bottom of inverted ungreased 8-inch cake pan to within 1/2-inch from sides.
Bake layers, two at a time at 425° for 5 minutes.
Trim uneven edges of circles; run a knife under pastry to loosen it from cake pans.
Invert layers onto wax paper to cool.

title: miniature cheeseburger pies
directions: Hollow out the 6 rolls, keeping the tops as little caps. Then fry
the chopped meat, adding generous amounts of peppers and onions
along
with the barbecue sauce.
Fry the mushrooms separately.
Then
stuff
the rolls topping them with the mushrooms and
cheese.
"Cap" them before placing them into an oven set at
for
to
minutes.
Allow them to cool for several minutes, then enjoy!

title: tropical fruit blush
directions: Boil water and Equal or sugar until sweetener dissolves.
Add orange juice, still frozen.
Stir until orange juice melts.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Stir in 7-Up.
After the foam goes down, stir again.

title: black forest trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool; cut into cubes.
Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Arrange 1/2 of the cake cubes in glass bowl.
Sprinkle cake in bowl with rum or brandy.
Layer 1/2 pudding, 1/2 cherry pie filling and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layering in order given.
Chill for at least 3 hours before serving.
Looks pretty in a tall stemmed bowl.

title: mock pink champagne
directions: Early in the day, mix sugar and water in saucepan and boil for 5 minutes.
Cool.
Add frozen concentrates.
Refrigerate.
At serving time, add ginger ale and grenadine syrup. Stir lightly.

title: crab dip
directions: Add milk to softened cream cheese.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Put mixture into baking dish.
Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ham appetizers
directions: Mix butter, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, poppy seed and onion.
Spread mix on each half of roll.
Put canned ham and Swiss cheese on bottom, put top half of roll back on and bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Put foil over top.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend together soup and milk and pour over sliced potatoes in a well-greased 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 375° (covered) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Uncover; bake an additional 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix everything together and fry in vegetable oil until golden brown.

title: raisin bran bread
directions: Stir scalded milk into cereal, shortening, molasses, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Dissolve dry yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Steam raisins in 1/4 cup water over medium heat; drain.
Add 2 cups flour to bran mixture; beat vigorously by hand.
Stir in yeast. Add raisins and remaining flour until dough forms around spoon.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut-caramel pie
directions: Bake pie shells according to package directions.
Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set aside.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup confectioners sugar.
Add 2 cups flour and mix well.
Pat into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix as for cake in order given.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: layer salad
directions: In high sided glass bowl, layer veggies in order given.
Top with frozen peas.
Spread mayonnaise on top of peas, spreading to edge of dish to "seal."
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with cheese. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, cook, drain and crumble bacon on top.

title: cheesy tortilla corn(serves 6)
directions: Cook onions and red peppers in 2 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Stir in corn and cheese.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes until cheese melts and mixture is heated.
Melt remaining 2 tablespoons margarine in separate pan and stir in seasoning and chips.
Cook 3 minutes over medium heat.
Spoon corn into bowl and top with tortilla mixture.

title: applesauce pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, butter, applesauce, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° until center is done.

title: e-z punch
directions: Serve over ice in a punch bowl.
Delicious for parties.

title: sweet and sour beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1 1/2 cups liquid. Set beets aside. Combine 1 1/2 cups beet liquid, sugar and remaining ingredients in a large saucepan, stirring with
a wire whisk until cornstarch is dissolved. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils. Boil 1 minute.
Remove cloves and stir in beets. Beets may be served warm or chilled.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-quart glass bowl or heat resistant glass punch bowl.
Microwave for 12 to 14 minutes on High, or until hot (about 160°).
Stir in rum.
Yields 25 to 30 (4-ounce) punch cups.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt and butter.
Add eggs and enough water to make dough.
On floured surface, roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut into strips and drop into boiling chicken broth.

title: broccoli-nut salad
directions: For dressing, in a small bowl, gradually stir vinegar and sugar into the mayonnaise until blended.

title: chocolate eclair ring
directions: Bring water and 1/2 cup butter to boil.
Reduce heat.
Stir all flour in at once.
Beat until ball forms.
Cool 10 minutes. Beat in eggs, one at a time until well blended.
Spoon onto baking sheet, forming a ring with sides touching.
Bake at 450° until lightly browned, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in draft-free place completely.

title: judy's bread
directions: *Teff is an Ethiopian grain high in protein and calcium. Gives nice taste.
Can be purchased at health food stores here in Moses Lake.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix pie filling and nuts.
Add drained pineapple, lemon juice and a dash of salt.
Add Cool Whip.
Put in covered dish and freeze.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco mix. Spread refried beans evenly over serving dish. Layer guacamole, then sour cream mixture. Top with the rest of your toppings. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: banana pudding
directions: Melt butter, add flour and sugar, mix.
Add milk and eggs. Cook slowly on low heat until thick.
Stir at all times.
Add vanilla.
Place in layers; bananas, pudding; repeat until all used, make sure pudding is on top.
Chill and serve.
Use chopped nuts on top if desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan in order listed.
Top with cooked bacon and cover tightly.
Store in refrigerator overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix both soups with Velveeta;
add broccoli.
Fold in 1 cup Cheez-Its.
Pour
into
a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheez-Its on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon-raisin cream cheese
directions: Lightly beat cream cheese with 1 to 2 tablespoons milk.
Add and mix ingredients well.
Serve with bagels, apple slices or frosting on a cake.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Let set.
Cover with topping.

title: good pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, two at a time.
Blend well.
Add 2 cups flour, then milk, then remaining flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend oil or melted butter, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs; using a spoon, beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool; frost with Creamy Brownie Frosting.
Cut into squares. Yields about 16 brownies.

title: "very veggie"  vegetable soup
directions: Warm oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and bell peppers. Cook 5 minutes or until tender. Add garlic and cumin. Cook 1 minute. Add cabbage, carrots, zucchini, squash, tomatoes (with juice), vegetable juice, black pepper and red pepper flakes. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 1 hour. This soup is so good and has only 170 calories per serving.

title: corned corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes in a greased pan or skillet.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Roll out crescent rolls.
Place on a pizza pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Spread onion dip over crust.
Prepare all other ingredients.
Mix.
Put on top of onion dip.
You can add or omit any fresh vegetable.

title: quick pepperoni spaghetti
directions: Combine onion, green pepper, ground beef and pepperoni in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until beef browns, stirring to crumble.
Remove from heat; drain and return to skillet.

title: apple butter
directions: Put
brown sugar, cinnamon and allspice in 6-quart cooker. Add half of applesauce (that has been put in blender to make it fine).
Stir ingredients until well blended, then fill cooker with rest of applesauce.
Cook about 24 hours on high until thick.
Lid must not be tight, leave 1/2 to inch space.
When cool, put in 1/2 pound margarine tubs and freeze.

title: john's punch
directions: Simmer the above ingredients for two hours.
Serve warm on a cool evening.
Tastes very much like the German's Gluervein I had in Munich.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Put in greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: over and under cake new orleans recipe
directions: Spread pecans in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish (or aluminum pan), then spread coconut.
Make German chocolate cake mix as directed on package.
Pour over coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese in a saucepan slowly, then add 4x sugar.
Mix well, then pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Be sure when you check it, it should spring back.
This has to be served from dish.
You will enjoy!

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat sugar, butter, eggs, flour and cocoa; mix, then add coconut, vanilla and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Put marshmallow cream on while cake is real hot.
Add frosting.

title: elephant stew
directions: Remove elephant tusks.
Skin and bone elephant.
Simmer in large vat for 2 months.
Add water every week.
At the end of 2 month period, add remaining ingredients and cook for 2 1/2 days.

title: 7-up red satin punch
directions: Chill fruit juices and 7-Up.
Prepare 7-Up ice cubes by pouring additional 7-Up into 2 ice cube trays.
Freeze.

title: stewed tomato casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, place melted margarine. Sprinkle bread crumbs over the margarine until they are about 1/4-inch thick.
Layer on the sliced onion, then green pepper. Evenly spread all of the chopped tomatoes, including all the juice, over the green pepper.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: In large bowl, toss potato wedges with lemon juice, oil and garlic.
Let stand for 30 minutes or longer to marinate.
Arrange wedges in single layer on 15 x 10 x 1-inch nonstick baking sheet. Drizzle remaining lemon oil mixture with dried parsley flakes over them.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes. Turn potato slices and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serve with lemon wedges and salsa to dip, if desired.

title: cottage cheese coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: sugar-free fudge
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add chocolate and stir just until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in sweetener and vanilla. Combine chocolate mixture with cream cheese and beat until smooth. Stir in nuts and spread mixture on lightly greased 8-inch square pan.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry beef, onion, garlic and seasonings.
Add tomatoes and sauce.
Simmer.
Add water and rice (may cook separately).
Cook until rice is done.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Chop
cabbage,	pepper and onion.
Add 2 cups sugar and toss. Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil. Pour
over cabbage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.	This will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat margarine, oil, sugar eggs, vanilla and sour milk with mixer.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; beat well. Stir in zucchini.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onions.
Mix cornbread as directed, adding a little sugar and extra milk.
Mix corn and tomatoes with hamburger meat.
Pour a little cornbread mixture in bottom of pan. Add a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Add hamburger mixture and a layer of Cheddar cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread down the middle of pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and water.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: napoleon cake
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan with layer of graham crackers.
With electric mixer, beat pudding with 2 cups milk until thick.
Clean beaters.
Whip 2 containers of cream until stiff.
Fold into pudding mixture.
Spread mixture evenly over graham crackers.
Top mixture with another layer of graham crackers.
Beat remaining cream until thick and spread over the crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.

title: old fashion caramels
directions: Cook on low heat, the sugar, milk and cocoa.
Cook until soft ball forms in water.
Add vanilla and butter, beat until stiff. Pour into a buttered, greased pan.

title: party meatballs and spaghetti for 8
directions: Mix beef, cheese, caraway seed, parsley, green pepper, beaten eggs, salt and pepper together.
Shape mixture into little meatballs about 1 inch in diameter.
Heat fat in large, heavy skillet.
Brown meat on all sides over low heat.
Cut garlic in pieces and cook with the meat.
Make sauce.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening. Add sugar, egg and applesauce. Use a little flour to dredge fruit and nuts. Set aside.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot baked stuffed clams
directions: Saute
garlic, onion, parsley, oregano and bread crumbs in oil
about	2
minutes, mixing thoroughly.	When onion and garlic start to brown, remove mixture from frying pan and mix with clams,
claim juice and salt.
Spoon into baking shells; sprinkle lightly
with
bread
crumbs
and
cheese.	Place on baking sheet.
Bake
at
for
25 to 30 minutes or until crusty on top.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add chopped onion and ketchup.
Place in baking dish.
Place Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.

title: hot hominy
directions: Heat soup and Velveeta until Velveeta melts.
Add drained hominy and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle crushed Fritos on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix together juice (given to you by a friend from her cake), 1 cup sugar and peaches.
Stir and let stand 1 week.
Add pineapple and 1 cup sugar.
Stir and let stand 1 week.
Add cherries and 1 cup sugar.
Stir and let stand 1 week.
Drain fruit through a large strainer.
Reserve juice to give to a friend for a cake.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Fold sugar into stiff egg mixtures. Mix in pecans. Melt butter in jelly roll pan. Bake in oven at 325° for 30 minutes. Stir pecans in pan every 10 minutes.

title: stuffed acorn squash
directions: About 2 hours before serving, heat oven to 350°.
In 10-inch skillet cook sausage until browned; drain.
Cut squash in 1/2 lengthwise.
Remove seed.
Place cut side up in large shallow roasting pan.
Brush inside with margarine.
Combine sausage, cheese, butter, vegetable and salt.
Spoon into squash that has been brushed with butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pink fruit punch
directions: Mix kool aid, water, and sugar to taste. Mix with other juices. Chill good before serving. It can be frozen.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix together last four ingredients.
Mix in blender.
Spread thin layer on tortilla.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice and serve with salsa.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Chop ham, onion and cheese. Add egg, mustard, and pepper, mix well.
Lightly spray mini muffin tin with Pam.
Cut biscuits into quarters, place each quarter into mini muffin tin.
Mash each one down using a wooden spoon dusted with flour.
Add above mixture.
Bake 13-15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal-peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend applesauce, peanut butter, honey, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, oatmeal, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Fold in nuts, if desired.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the oil in a large skillet over medium heat. Add the zucchini and saute until just tender, 5 to 7 minutes. Transfer the zucchini to a large, flameproof casserole or Dutch oven.
Add fresh tomatoes.
Heat the remaining 1/4 cup of oil in the skillet over low heat.
Add the onions, garlic and bell peppers.
Saute until just wilted, about 10 minutes.
Transfer the mixture to the casserole along with the oil remaining in the skillet.
Place the casserole over low heat.
Add the canned tomatoes and their juice, the fresh tomatoes, chili powder, cumin, basil, oregano, pepper, salt, fennel seed and parsley.
Cook, uncovered, stirring often for 30 minutes.
Stir in the kidney beans, chickpeas, dill and lemon juice; cook for another 15 minutes.
Stir well and adjust the seasonings to taste.
Serve with bowls of sour cream, grated cheese and sliced scallions along side.
Garnish with black beans.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix
sugar,
water and cornstarch; cook until it thickens. Cool
and
mix
in the Jell-O gelatin.
Pour over sliced peaches. When
ready to serve, top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain. Mix taco seasoning and beans (with juice) into hamburger. Crumble chips in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Pour meat mixture over chips and bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top and heat until melted. Serves 4 to 6.

title: irish dumplings
directions: Heat fat in frying pan.
Add onion and saute until golden brown.
Add grated potatoes.
Cook until mixture forms a paste. Let cool.
Add potatoes, salt, flour and eggs.
Stir until smooth. Form into balls the size of a walnut.
Drop into boiling salted water.
Cook until dumplings rise to the top and are cooked through center, about 15 minutes.
Drain.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add the sugars, mixing well.
Mix dry ingredients with the oil and pumpkin, stirring until well combined.
Add eggs, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Wait 5 minutes, then remove from pans.

title: marinated green beans
directions: Drain green beans (whole). Pour Zesty Italian dressing over beans. Marinate overnight. Next day, drain and put 4 or 5 beans in a bundle. Wrap with bacon and bake in oven at 425° until bacon is done.

title: indian curried chicken
directions: In a large bowl, heat the oil.
Add onions, garlic and ginger. Saute for a minute.

title: sausage cheddar quiche
directions: Cook sausage until browned; drain.
Combine sausage with next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Top with shredded cheese.
Combine milk and eggs and beat until foamy. Pour evenly over sausage mixture; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until cheese is lightly brown and quiche is set.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cool.
Cut cheese and pepperoni in bite-size pieces.
Slice olives.
Dice green pepper, celery and onion.
Add to pasta.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, oil and vinegar. Combine all ingredients except tomatoes.
Chill overnight.
Add diced tomatoes just before serving.

title: mother's chess pie
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: pecan pralines
directions: In a 3-quart heavy saucepan, combine granulated sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat for 5 minutes or to 210° on candy thermometer.
Stir often and scrape bottom.
Mixture will foam up.
Add butter or margarine and pecans.
Over medium heat, continue cooking, stirring constantly and scraping bottom and sides of pan, until candy makes a soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat; cool slightly, about 2 minutes. Beat with spoon until thick and creamy.
Spoon onto wax paper about 2 inches in diameter.

title: sour cream pie
directions: Mix and cook in double boiler.
Pour into a baked pie shell.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Combine crumbs and butter in a buttered casserole.
Drain oysters.
Put layer of oysters over crumbs.
Alternate layer of oysters and crumbs.
Sprinkle each layer with a little salt. (Never use more than 2 layers oysters.)
Mix oyster liquor with the milk and cream of mushroom soup and pour over top.
Top with buttered crumbs and bake in 450° oven for 30 minutes.

title: racy red punch
directions: Heat 1 cup of juice.
Add candies and sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add remaining juice off heat.
Allow to cool thoroughly.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with 1 sleeve of Town House crackers (crushed).
Drizzle with 1 stick melted margarine.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and microwave 15 more minutes.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in pan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add jello stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and stir until combined.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans (12 x 8 x 2-inch dish).
Chill.

title: sugar baked ham
directions: Trim rind and fat off ham.
Score ham in crisscross fashion. Stud with cloves and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Put sugar onto ham.
Bake 15 minutes to the pound. If sugar crust gets too brown, cover with foil.

title: banana pops
directions: You will need 6 wooden sticks.

title: chili in pastry cups
directions: Cook ground beef, green pepper and onion in a skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat.
Drain meat.
Add tomatoes and next 5 ingredients, stirring well.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve hot in Cornmeal Pastry Cups.
Makes 4 dozen appetizers.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain the juice from the can of pineapple and dissolve the jello with the juice.
Bring to a boil.
Mix pineapple with cottage cheese.
Pour jello mixture into cottage cheese mixture. Set to chill.
Add cherries and pecans to chilled mixture.
Whip cream rather stiff.
Fold into cottage cheese mixture.
Set to firm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions, then drain.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix milk, mayo and soup together; pour over meat. Cover the top with cheese and place Tater Tots on top of cheese. Cook at 350° until golden brown.

title: doodlebug soup
directions: Put all into pot, being careful of deer tracks because you just can't find them anytime.
Cook until done and you can't wait any longer.
Serve with a sprig of parsley on top.
Happy eating.

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip and stir together.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place a layer of graham crackers.
Pour half the pudding mix on top.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
Pour remaining pudding on top.
Add another layer of graham crackers. Put frosting on top of graham crackers.
Refrigerate.
Let set overnight or several hours before serving.

title: good dill pickles
directions: Boil the vinegar, water and salt together for 3 minutes.
Put cucumbers in jar with 2 sprigs of dill, small piece of garlic bud (in each jar).
I put thin slice of jalapeno pepper in some of mine.
Pour the vinegar mixture over cucumbers in the jars.
Seal. Let stand for 6 weeks before opening.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook hamburg until brown.
Drain off fat.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Cook until soft.
Add soup, paste, water and seasonings.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes or longer.

title: smoked wild turkey 2
directions: Soak turkey in cold water for 3 hours to remove excess blood. Rub turkey with salt, pepper, sage and butter or margarine.
Place garlic and onions inside breast and splash cavity with Sauterne. Place on water smoker rack.
Add pecan or hickory chips to coals. Cook, covered, until coals die, usually 10 to 12 hours.

title: chorizo(mexican sausage)
directions: Mix all dry spices in blender.
Then add garlic, cilantro, jalapenos and vinegar.
Blend in large bowl.
Mix pork with all blended ingredients.
Fry as sausage patties.

title: taco bubble pizza
directions: Bake hamburger in microwave 5 minutes.
Cut biscuits in fourths.
Grease a medium roasting pan.
Set oven at 400°.
Put biscuits in bottom of pan.
Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix to hamburger and pour over the biscuits.
Cover with cheese and put in oven for 15 minutes.
Put the other ingredients on top when you bring out of
the oven.

title: white mushroom sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in water until soft.
Add rest of ingredients except cornstarch, bring to a boil, stirring often. Blend cornstarch with 1/3 cup cool water.
Add to white sauce and cook until thickened.

title: grandma's sweet and sauerkraut
directions: Dice bacon and chop onion.
Brown in heavy skillet and pour off grease.
Add all other ingredients as listed and mix.
Do not drain kraut or tomatoes.
Place in 2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: baked crispy chicken thighs
directions: *Or use chicken parts and adjust cooking time accordingly.

title: raindrop raspberry iced tea
directions: In large saucepan, bring 4 cups water to boil.
Remove from the heat.
Add tea bags; steep for 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags. Add sugar.
Add ice cold water and juice concentrate; mix well. Serve over ice.
Garnish with a twist of lemon.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour onion soup mix over roast and rub in gently.
Peel and quarter potatoes and carrots and arrange over the meat.
Pour water over meat and cover and bake about 1 1/2 hours until done through.
Tender and delicious.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Pour oil into package of oyster crackers.
Shake to coat crackers.
Pour dressing mix (dry) in also.
Shake all well.
Put into another bag and tie.
Will keep fresh for days.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, ginger and baking soda.
Mix all ingredients together and place in refrigerator for about 1 hour or overnight.
Roll thick, about 1/4-inch and cut with cookie cutters. Bake in 350° to 375° oven for 8 to 12 minutes.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Mix all together; let set a while and spoon off "water" from top 2 to 3 times.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate several hours (at least) before using.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli according to package directions.
Cook onion, butter and celery until tender.
Mix rest of ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
I put crushed cheese crackers on top before baking (I use Cheese Nips or goldfish crackers).
Serves 8 to 12.

title: hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger with onions, cut small, until tender. Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: sausage and hash brown casserole
directions: Brown the sausage.
Drain.
Combine the cheese, soup, sour cream, onion dip, onions, peppers, salt, and pepper. Fold in hash browns. Mix well.
Spread 1/2 of the potato mixture over the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Spread 1/2 of browned sausage over hash browns.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: swiss eggs
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients; add salt as desired.
Put bread cubes on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over bread.
Sprinkle onion, pepper and mushrooms on top.
Pour egg mixture slowly over top.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pasta carbonara
directions: Boil noodles while frying bacon in butter.
Mix whipping cream and eggs in bowl with salt and pepper.
Add Parmesan cheese last. Drain noodles and put back in pot.
Add crumbled bacon and all other ingredients.
Keep pot on stove on high heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Must be served hot as soon as cooking has completed.
Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Thaw fish, if frozen.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for dressing.
Just before serving, pour over remaining ingredients.
Serve and enjoy.

title: welsh rarebit(serves two)
directions: Put the ale into a saucepan and melt the cheese in it slowly. Add the pepper, salt, mustard and the butter.
When thoroughly hot, pour the mixture on the freshly made toast.
Place under the broiler until lightly browned and serve.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, melt shortening and brown pork chops.
Drain on paper towels.
In buttered 2-quart oblong baking dish, arrange potatoes, onion and chops. Top with mushrooms and pepper.
In a small bowl, combine dry soup mix and water.
Pour over vegetables and meat.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour or until potatoes and chops are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix together butter and shortening.
Cream together sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Sift and add flour, soda and baking powder. Blend in oatmeal, coconut, chopped nuts, chocolate chips and corn flakes.
Use 1/4 cup measuring cup to drop on cookie sheet.
Six cookies to a sheet.
Don't flatten out dough.
It will go down by itself.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: fingerpaint
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch, add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly.
Divide mixture into 4 or 5 portions and add a few drops of food coloring to each; plus a pinch of laundry detergent.
(This will facilitate cleaning up!)

title: molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening and allow to cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Chill batter.

title: never fail cornbread
directions: Melt margarine and honey together.
Cool a bit.
Combine buttermilk and eggs.
Add to the margarine and honey mixture.
Put dry ingredients into a bowl and stir.
Add wet mixture to dry ingredients until moistened.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch square.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients by hand.
Shape into walnut size meatballs.
Fry on all sides until brown.
Remove from pan, saving drippings.
Cool drippings slightly and add soup, stirring briskly with a wire whisk.
Stir in milk and half and half.
Add more milk if needed to obtain a gravy.
Return meatballs to gravy and heat through.
Serve over egg noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oil and sugar until light.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Sift together dry ingredients; add dry ingredients and milk to first mixture and flavorings.
Bake at 325° or 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta with zucchini and tomatoes
directions: Boil pasta.
While pasta is cooking, saute garlic in oil and add basil, zucchini and tomatoes.
Cover and let simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.
Put over pasta and serve.

title: broiled shrimp scampi appetizers
directions: Peel and clean raw shrimp.
In large skillet melt butter and lightly toss shrimp 5 to 7 minutes, until cooked with garlic powder.
Fry bacon until "chewy" and cut into pieces large enough to wrap around shrimp.
Serve with toothpicks.
Right before serving, put under broiler to heat.

title: hot crab-shrimp dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise and cream cheese in mixer until down to small lumps.
Drain shrimp and crab thoroughly; fold into mix.
Place in baking dish (9 x 13 x 3-inch).
Cover with slivered almonds.
Bake 30 minutes in 350°
oven.
Cool.
Reheat in microwave 3 minutes before serving.
Serve with crackers (Sociables seem to taste best).
Do not use crackers with distinctive flavor of their own or heavily salted.
Serves:
Lots.

title: a-1 sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, cook and crumble meat until brown; drain. Add to meat the tomato sauce, onion, catsup, steak sauce and garlic salt.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: joann's coffee cake
directions: Spray tube pan with Pam.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Dip biscuits, one at a time, in butter, then into dry ingredients, coating each side.
Stand up in tube pan to form a circle. Sprinkle with leftover dry ingredients and pour remaining butter over biscuits.
Bake at 375° approximately 30 minutes.
Glaze while still hot.

title: quick strawberry pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender, except graham crust and mix well.
Put in graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Take out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: ham quiche
directions: Line a 9-inch dish with pastry.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes. Prick with a fork and cook 5 minutes longer.
Combine mayo, flour, eggs and milk.
Mix.
Stir in ham, cheeses and mushrooms.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef, chopped onion and green pepper.
Add garlic salt, oregano and black pepper.
Add tomato sauce and beans and mixed vinegar and sugar.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers and cole slaw or salad.
A good one dish meal.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: vanilla frosting(frosts two 8 or 9-inch layers or a 13 x 9-inch cake)
directions: In a bowl, mix Crisco, salt, vanilla and about 1/3 of the sugar.
Add milk and remaining sugar alternately.
Mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin frosting, if needed, for good spreading consistency.

title: sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: veal patties
directions: Chop onions.
Mince basil.
Add green onions and half of basil to beaten egg whites.
Stir in veal, bread crumbs and 1/4 cup milk.
Add nutmeg, allspice and pepper.
Make patties.
Brown in olive oil.
Remove to plate and keep warm.
Combine 1/2 cup milk and flour; blend.
In skillet, add chicken stock and bring to a boil, stirring browned bits from bottom of pan.
Stir in flour mixture; cook 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining basil.
Return patties to skillet.
Cook two minutes until hot.
Good with brown rice and green vegetable.

title: rice krispies chicken
directions: Melt
butter
or
margarine.
Dip
chicken
into melted butter or
margarine,
then
coat with crushed Rice Krispies. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes (depending on the amount of chicken used).

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening or margarine and sugar.
Beat in the egg until light.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg to creamed mixture.
Add mashed bananas, vanilla and the quick Quaker oats and nuts.
Mix to blend.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased and floured baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: something special-hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in an oven-safe dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Transfer to chafing dish and serve with cubed French bread or crackers.
This may be made the day before, but do not cook until serving time.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan and heat until the cheese melts.
Serve with your favorite chips.

title: creole beans
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Stir all ingredients into beans. Simmer 20 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top when served.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend thoroughly.
Chill well.
Serve in cold mugs or bowls.
Add seasoned croutons and paprika.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed ground turkey patties
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well and shape into 12 thin patties.
Combine green pepper, green onion and mushrooms; spoon 2 rounded tablespoons of vegetables on top of half of the patties. Top each with half a cheese slice and a remaining patty, sealing edges.
Wrap bacon around each patty, tucking in under bottom. Place patties on greased broiler rack. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Place under broiler for an additional 2 minutes or until bacon is brown.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except almonds and paprika.
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with almonds and sprinkle with paprika.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place pieces in greased baking dish (13 x 9). Brown sausage in skillet. Drain off fat. Cut links in slices. Spoon sausage over bread. Sprinkle with cheese. Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper. Pour over mixture in baking dish. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Cheese will rise to top during baking.

title: peanut butter crunchies
directions: Boil honey, syrup and sugar for 1 minute. Mix in peanut butter, corn flakes and vanilla. Drop on waxed paper. Eat as soon as cool enough.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Combine pumpkin with ice cream.
Combine sugar with spices; add to ice cream mixture.
Pour into crust; top with pecans, if desired.
Freeze until serving time.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Put broccoli and rice in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir in 1/2 Cheez Whiz.
Melt butter in a skillet; add onion and celery and cook until tender.
Stir in milk, soup, salt and pepper.
Top with remaining Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt cille's baked chicken salad
directions: Toss lightly all ingredients except crushed potato chips, grated American cheese, and chopped almonds.
Spoon into casserole.
Spread the potato chips, cheese, and almonds on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Will serve 22 people.

title: c r w r c french toast
directions: Melt oleo in large cookie sheet.
Sprinkle over oleo the brown sugar and cinnamon.
Mix and dip bread into eggs and milk.
Lay bread on cookie sheet.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken; debone and set aside, reserving broth.
To 7 cups chicken broth, add onion, bell pepper, celery, poultry seasoning and salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add raw rice; adjust heat and cover.
Cook until rice is done.
Add deboned chicken; simmer.
Serve and enjoy.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: firehouse casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Add soup, milk and peppers after hamburger meat has been drained.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cut tortillas in strips and line baking dish.
Put 1/2 hamburger mixture over tortillas and put 1/2 cheeses on top of hamburger mixture. Repeat.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: banana-chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly butter muffin tins.
Stir together dry ingredients.
With mixer, beat butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then stir in vanilla extract, banana and milk.
Don't panic when this looks curdled. Add dry ingredients and stir to combine.
Reserving 2 tablespoons of nuts and 2 tablespoons of chocolate chips for garnish, stir in remaining ingredients.
Spoon into muffin tins, then sprinkle tops with nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 to 10 minutes on a rack.
Remove muffins and cool on a rack.

title: cocktail vienna bread
directions: Place foil on cookie sheet-put bread on top-slice bread.

Put stuffing on top of bread and push in between (fingers) of bread. Prepare to this point-wrap foil around bread and refrigerate. Before baking, open foil and top with mixture of - 1/2 cup melted butter, 1 1/2 tbsp. lemon juice and 1 tbsp. dry mustard.
Seal and heat for 40 minutes at 350 degrees.
You can also cut across and then down the middle.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix lemonade, Cool Whip and chilled milk until smooth.
Pour mixture into pie shell and chill 1 hour before serving.

title: parfait
directions: Heat milk and gelatin until gelatin is dissolved and smooth. Stir in yogurt and half of the whipped cream.
Layer in parfait glasses with fruit and remaining whipped cream.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all the dry ingredients. Set aside. In another bowl, beat egg and mix with sour cream, milk and butter. Add to cornmeal mixture. Mix just until combined.
