Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking dish or muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tests done and golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream
shortening,
sugar
and eggs; beat until fluffy. Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in deep loaf pan in 325° oven 1 hour or until brown.

title: fruit cake cups
directions: Mix together raisins, margarine and orange juice.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cool and add marmalade.
Mix in other liquid, egg, nuts and fruit.
Sift together dry ingredients and fold in last.
Add cherries and nuts for garnish (optional).
Cook in small muffin tins at 300° for 30 minutes or more depending on size of tins. Makes 18 to 36.
Fill tins 2/3 to 3/4 full.
Store tightly covered in tin or plastic container.
Keeps well.

title: berry dips
directions: Mix 1/2 of Cool Whip and orange peel in small bowl.
Mix rest of Cool Whip, strawberries and yogurt in separate bowl.
Dip whole strawberries, melon, etc. and pound cake into mixture.
Store leftover dip in refrigerator.
Makes 5 1/4 cups.

title: spring huckleberry pie
directions: Use 9-inch deep dish pie pan.
Toss berries with melted butter or margarine, flour and sugar.
Mix until berries are coated. Fill pie crust with filling.
Top with crust and cut vents.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until berries boil out top and crust is brown.

title: sauce for harvard beets
directions: Cook until clear.
Add 1 teaspoon of butter after sauce is
in beets (strain beets first).
One-half of recipe is good for 1 can of beets.

title: russian pelmeni
directions: Mix together the meats, onion, salt and pepper.

title: five-bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain beans and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Brown sausage in a skillet over medium heat.
Remove sausage and drain grease, reserving a small amount in skillet.

title: bran bucket of muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together Raisin Bran, flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate, stored in closed container.
Will keep 6 weeks.
Entire recipe makes 6 dozen medium-sized muffins.
Can use as much as you wish each time.
Bake in muffin tins for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked camembert antipasto(this baked cheese is really an elegant fondue.)
directions: On a large serving platter, wooden tray or low rimmed basket, arrange rinsed and dried grapes, chunks of bread, small bowls of olives and the bread sticks, leaving room for the baked cheese.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Break pretzels into bite-size pieces.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: goblin-choco cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a saucepan, melt chocolate and butter; let cool. In a bowl, mix flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until pale yellow and slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients and cook until thick.
Add egg yolks, flour, milk and vanilla.
Add this to the syrup mixture and cook until thick; then cool.
Pour in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake until brown.

title: cherry wink cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and cream cheese.
Add shortening, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and almond extract; beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture.
Chill 1 hour.

title: corn dog and fried shrimp batter
directions: Mix well.
Dip franks into batter.
Fry in deep fat for about 2 minutes or until batter is golden brown.

title: corn chip salad
directions: Break lettuce into bite-size pieces.
Mix all ingredients except corn chips and dressing, which should be added just before serving.
Serves many.

title: play dough
directions: Mix salt and flour, set aside.
Mix water, salad oil and food coloring.
Add to salt and flour.
If too sticky, add flour or if too dry, add water.
Keep in jars (capped) between uses. Consistency of clay.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Layer items in 9 x 13 pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Can be made one day ahead, but add 1/2 cup of water before reheating.

title: broccoli cheese
directions: While broccoli is thawing in one cup of water that has been brought to a boil, saute onions and celery in butter.
Add soup and soup can of milk to onions and celery, then add Cheez Whiz. Simmer for a minute or so, then add thawed broccoli, rice and seasoning.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in oven.

title: old-fashioned chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender (about 1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Let chicken cool in broth if possible.
Remove from broth and take off the bone in pieces.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with chicken pieces.
Top with peas and carrots and corn.

title: carmel valley wells fargo
directions: Brown bacon.
Add onion, celery, tomatoes and chicken stock; simmer for 30 minutes.
Add flour to thicken (we prefer it on the thin side).
Add to gumbo powder, cooked chicken and okra.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or as a soup.

title: crunchy beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients (except onions).
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with French fried onions and bake 5 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Cut
cucumbers
lengthwise
into
halves; remove seeds. Cut each
half
into
1/2-inch
slices.
Mix cucumbers, soup, water chestnuts
and milk in 3 quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until cucumbers are tender, about 6 minutes.
Stir in dill weed and pimento.

title: fettuccine supreme(only 267 calories per serving)
directions: In blender container combine Ricotta cheese and milk and process until smooth; set aside.
In 9-inch skillet heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add Prosciutto and garlic and saute until garlic is golden, about 1 minute.
Add broccoli and cheese mixture and cook over medium heat until sauce begins to bubble.
Reduce heat and add remaining ingredients except parsley.
Cook, stirring and tossing gently until fettuccine is thoroughly coated with sauce.
Serve sprinkled with parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. Spread on tortilla shells; add vegetables. Roll up and refrigerate 2 hours. Cut into 1-inch pieces.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
This prevents pasta from sticking together.
Let cool.
Mix vegetables into macaroni using enough Italian dressing to make pasta moist.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese heavily or to taste over pasta.
Mix well.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Better after setting for awhile.

title: scramble ham and cheese egg
directions: Scramble eggs.
Cut ham and cheese into small pieces.
Add to eggs and cook.
Butter pan and cook for 5 minutes with low heat. Mix while cooking.

title: cranberry raisin cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars. Add eggs, then other stuff. Bake at 350° (I like them underdone). Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, syrup, flour or cornstarch, salt and melted butter. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Top with pecans and bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cream gravy
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in flour, until well blended. Add 1 cup milk.
Season to taste.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Beat egg whites with water until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and rest of ingredients except pecans.
Beat until thick, but not stiff.
Add nuts, stirring gently.
Pour out onto cookie sheet, lined with foil, then greased.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, until lightly browned.
Remove from foil immediately.
Place on waxed paper.
Separate nuts with fork.
When cool, store in tightly sealed container.

title: pita pizza
directions: Preheat broiler.
Brush bread lightly with oil.
Add sauce, toppings and cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Peel, slice and core carrots, peppers, cucumbers, tomatoes and onion.
Grind these up.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight. Drain.
Combine these ingredients with vinegar.
Tie cayenne pepper and spices in cheesecloth.
Add to the other mixture.
Pour into hot, clean jars after it has been brought to a boil.
Seal the jars.
Yields 6 pints.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Press in pie dish (13 x 9-inch) and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cereal
directions: Mix together oil and honey.
Put the first 6 ingredients in bowl and mix with oil and honey, then add cool water.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 225°.
Add almonds and cook 1/2 hour longer.
Stir every 15 to 20 minutes.
While warm, add raisins.

title: poulet grille farci au citron(lemon broiled chicken)
directions: Wipe the chicken carefully and split it in two; use a good sturdy knife, insert the point at the tip of the breast and press down firmly with both hands.
Quite easy really!
Rub both pieces well with salt and pepper and about 1 tablespoon of butter.
Place rather low under the preheated broiler and cook, basting frequently with a little butter and lemon juice, until it turns a beautiful golden color.
About 15 minutes should do it.

title: uncle norm's pancakes
directions: For thinner batter, add 3 cups milk rather than 2 1/2 cups.

title: no bake breakfast bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, honey and brown sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in cereal and fruit. Spread on greased (with Pam spray) 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish. Cool 15 minutes before cutting into bars.
Makes 18 bars.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Place in a 2-quart greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix crackers with margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan; pack it down.
Save some crumbs to sprinkle on top of cake.

title: worms
directions: In a bowl, combine the Jell-O, gelatin and water. Stir until gelatin is completely dissolved. Chill until lukewarm (about 20 minutes). While Jell-O is cooling, unwrap and extend the straws. Place upright in an empty and clean milk carton. Blend whipping cream, food coloring and lukewarm gelatin mixture. Pour into the milk container, filling the straws. CHILL AT LEAST 8 HOURS. Pull carton away from the straws. Pull straws apart. Run hot tap water for 2 seconds over 3-4 straws at a time. Starting at the empty end, push worms from straws. Lay worms on wax paper-lined cookie sheets. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Fix Jiffy cornbread mix as directed on package.
Crumble the bread.
Line a 2-quart dish with half of the bread.
Set aside. Cook the bacon until crisp. Drain well on paper towels.
Cut up the vegetables into bite size pieces.
Crumble bacon over the cornbread mix, then add the vegetable slices.
Mix mayonnaise and sweet pickles. Spread over the bacon and vegetables.
Sprinkle the rest of the bread on top.
Best if made the day before and refrigerated.

title: how to preserve a husband
directions: Be careful in selecting.
Do not choose one too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist on keeping them in a pickle; others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Even poor varieties may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well sweetened with love and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Mix broccoli and next 3 ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese pie
directions: Leave cream cheese out until soft.
Then put Cool Whip in and fold or stir until smooth.
Add berries and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first six ingredients well.
Pour into a well-greased, 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle or sift dry cake mix on top of pie mix.
Melt margarine and pour over top of dry cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple snack
directions: Let cheese stay at room temperature.
Drain pineapple.
Mix together with beater.
Spread or dip with Ritz crackers or all-purpose crackers.
Great anytime, especially sitting around the fire watching a good movie.

title: old fashioned nut cake
directions: Lightly grease bottom and sides of 10-inch tube pan.
Line with brown paper; grease paper.
Turn nuts into large bowl.
On waxed paper sift flour with baking powder and salt; set aside. Combine milk with rum.
Preheat oven to 275°.
In large bowl of electric mixer at medium speed, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each egg until light and fluffy.
At low speed beat in flour mixture, alternately with milk mixture, begin and end with flour.
Pour batter over nuts; mix well with large spoon.
Turn batter into pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 2 1/2 hours. Let cake cool on wire rack 30 minutes.
Turn out on rack, gently remove paper.
Let cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut cake into very thin slices.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in hot water.
Add cold water and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until set.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot water and add marshmallows.
Stir to melt.
Add pineapple, juice and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Fold in whipped cream and pour on lime Jell-O.
Let set.
Dissolve cherry Jell-O in hot water, add cool water.
Let this cool.
When cool, pour on set white layer.
Serve when set.

title: hanne's leftovers
directions: In ovenproof pan, melt butter.
Simmer onions until glazy; add mushrooms (sliced) and celery (diced).
Add cooked pasta, whipping cream and leftover meat or tuna.
Stir and season to taste.
Top with cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4. Any type of salad is a perfect side dish.

title: chocolate cake pudding
directions: Sift
3/4 cup sugar, flour, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and
salt	together
in
a 9-inch square pan.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla.
Spread evenly in pan.

title: squash-apple bake
directions: Arrange squash in an 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Top with apple wedges.
Combine remaining ingredients; spoon over apples.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until tender.

title: creamy-nutty tuna sandwiches
directions: Blend together cream cheese, lemon juice and mayonnaise until smooth.
Fold in olives, then tuna, then pecans.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine drained broccoli, onion and herb stuffing.
Place in 2-quart greased casserole.
Dribble butter over top.
Combine soups and spoon over broccoli mixture; do not mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove; cover and continue baking for 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: sauerkraut dish
directions: Peel potatoes and cube them; boil until soft.
Mash in a 13 x 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Mix kraut, mushroom soup and mayonnaise together.
Cut wieners bite size and mix with kraut. Pour over mashed potatoes.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup flour.
Combine and stir 1 1/4 cups flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Combine milk, Scramblers and oil.
Beat with a rotary beater until well mixed. Make a well in center of dry ingredients; add wet ingredients and stir until moistened.
Do not overmix.
Combine reserved flour and 1/2 cup whole frozen blueberries.
Toss.
Fold into batter and mix just until blueberries are evenly distributed.
Fill margarine-coated 2 1/2-inch muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.
Remove from cups.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or microwave.
Batter keeps up to 6 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a boiler.
Cover; reduce heat after bringing to boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk.
Heat thoroughly.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: one and one casserole
directions: Crumble ground meat in a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with rice and soup mix. Blend mushroom soup and water. Pour over rice. Spread onion tops over mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: orange cake
directions: Make cake
using
first
recipe
on back of box.
Grate oranges on	fine
side
of	grater	and set aside.	Mix sugar, margarine and
milk
together.
Cook
in
double boiler (as it scorches easy).
Let come to a full rolling boil that can't be stirred down; cook	2 to 3 minutes.
Take off stove and set in sink with
cold
water in it.
Stir until it thickens and gets cool.
Stir in grated orange peel and spread between layers.

title: green jello salad
directions: Mix lime gelatin and pineapple with juice in saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool. Stir in pecans and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate until well chilled.
Top with lemon gelatin which has been prepared according to package directions.

title: crisp pie crust
directions: Sift flour; add shortening and salt.
Blend until like coarse meal.
Add egg, water and vinegar.
Press together; do not knead. Makes 4 crusts.
Stor in refrigerator until needed.

title: dilly casserole bread
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Heat cottage cheese to lukewarm. Combine in mixing bowl cottage cheese, sugar, onion, egg and softened yeast.
Add flour to form a stiff dough, beating well after each addition.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85° to 90°) until light and double in size (50 or 60 minutes).
Stir dough down.
Turn into a well greased 8-inch round 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Let rise in a warm place until light, 30 or 40 minutes. Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Makes one round loaf.

title: mama's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken into joints, season with poultry seasoning and stew for 1 hour in salted boiling water with poultry seasoning, half the carrots and celery and one of the onions until tender. Remove chicken.
Strain stock and discard the vegetables. Add water to stock to make 6 cups.
Add remaining vegetables; bring to a boil.

Blend flour, salt and baking powder. Combine milk and egg with dry ingredients, making a soft sticky dough. When chicken broth is boiling, drop dumpling batter, 1/2 teaspoon of dough at a time. Cover and boil for 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with a little cold water.
Stir into simmering pot and return chicken. Simmer. Stir until chicken is hot and gravy is clear.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Combine shredded chicken, water chestnuts, bean sprouts and green onions in large bowl; set aside.

title: smoky corn chowder
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add the milk all at once; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in corn, sausage and lima beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Chop vegetables and set aside.
Scramble eggs and set aside. Cut meat.
Saute 1 tablespoon cooking oil with each different vegetable and set aside.

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a baking pan. Dip chicken in melted margarine. Coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve each flavor of gelatin separately in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 3/4 cup cold water to the cherry gelatin.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; chill until set.
Blend lemon gelatin mixture into softened cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Add pineapple with syrup.
Blend in Cool Whip and mayonnaise; mix well.
Pour this mixture over red layer; chill until set.
Mix 3/4 cup cold water to lime gelatin; chill slightly.
Pour over lemon mixture. Chill until firm, at least overnight.
Makes 8 cups or 16 servings.

title: pecan dream
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream in powdered sugar with the oleo. Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes. When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: betsy's pizza pies
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add pork and beans, onion, catsup, chili pepper, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic salt.

title: strawberry glace pie
directions: Layer berries in cooled crust.
In a medium saucepan, mix together all other ingredients and cook for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Pour hot sauce over berries and refrigerate until cool. Serve with whipped cream.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger meat and onions in skillet.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and simmer for 4 hours.

title: smooth and peachy
directions: Place all the ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.

title: whole wheat scones
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in margarine.
Add milk and mix with fork to form soft dough.

title: grilled nacho cheeseburgers
directions: Sprinkle 1 side of each frozen ground beef patty with garlic pepper.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together
and bake 25 minutes in an 8-inch square pan at 350°.
Serve
with
cocktail rye or snack crackers.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: In saucepan, mix apple juice, flour and cinnamon.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in sweetener.
Pour into pie shell and fill with apples; stir slightly.
Cover with second pie shell; cut vents. Bake at 350° until crust is golden.
May sprinkle crust with cinnamon before baking.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit:
kiwi, strawberries, etc.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cobana bars
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder, salt, instant coffee and sugar.
Add lemon extract and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool in pan and cut into bars, 4 inches long and 1 inch wide.
Frost with powdered sugar icing and sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Makes 24 bars.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well. Pour into a lightly greased 10 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Mix zucchini and sugar together and set 10 minutes.
Boil 10 minutes; stir.
Add Jell-O.
Pour into containers and store in refrigerator.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and onion; boil until tender and drain; cool.
Melt margarine in dish and brown lightly under broiler.
Reserve 1 cup dressing.
Mix all ingredients together and place in buttered dish.
Sprinkle remaining cup dressing on top.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles around the edge.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix ingredients. Make into round cakes using hands to shape. Fry in a little fat from sausage or fatback.

title: bread pudding
directions: Tear bread in pieces and place in ungreased 3 qt casserole. Pour boiling water over raisins, drain.
Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, cinnamon, nutmeg, and salt in mixing bowl.
Mix in raisins and pour over bread.
Bake about 1 hour 325° oven.
Serve with topping.

title: sausage bread
directions: Thaw dough.
Roll to 1/2-inch thick.
Spread with sausage and cheese.
Bring sides together and pinch to seal.
Place seam side down on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling and milk in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture begins to simmer.
Add butter and chocolate chips.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a full boil and all chips are melted.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
(Cover with plastic wrap.)
Generously spread Cool Whip before serving.

title: fiesta casserole
directions: In microwave-safe 2-quart casserole, cook meat on High for 5 minutes stirring after 2 minutes.
Drain off fat; place meat in bowl.
Add taco seasoning mix.
Stir until combined.

title: cajun seafood salad(ultra low-fat)
directions: Combine Italian dressing and mustard and stir until blended. In another bowl, combine remaining ingredients; add dressing. Chill and serve.

title: minestrone
directions: Brown sausage in deep saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil; cook for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, bouillon, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add beans, rice and wine, then cook another 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Place meat in casserole.
Pour rest of ingredients over the top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cottage cheese fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: roasted vegetable platter *
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Coat 2 cookie sheets or jelly roll pans with olive oil spray.
Cut a thin slice on top and bottom of onion and cut a deep tic-tac-toe (#) into the onion without cutting through bottom.
Place onion and vegetables onto pans and spray everything lightly (or drizzle with bottled olive oil).
Sprinkle with herbs.
Roast at 475° for 35 minutes.
Shake pans gently halfway through to prevent sticking.

title: sausage-apple balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets; bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: ice cream sundae
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar and set aside. Mix pineapple, strawberries, bananas and nuts together.
Add cheese mixture. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour in lined loaf pan (use foil to line pan) and freeze.
To serve, cut slices.
This keeps a long time in freezer.

title: peach bread
directions: Combine scalded milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.

title: larimer toffee squares
directions: Line 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan with foil and place whole graham crackers in single layer on foil.
In small saucepan, heat butter and brown sugar until sugar dissolves.
Spread evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes and transfer to wax paper to cool completely.

title: broken glass tart
directions: Dissolve each package of the lime, raspberry and lemon jellos in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Chill until firm.
Cut in 1/2-inch cube squares.

title: icebox cake
directions: Line a long cake pan with a mixture of the cracker crumbs and melted margarine.
(Save 1/4 cup of the cracker crumb mixture out for the topping.)
Mix milk, lemon juice, egg yolks and vanilla. Beat egg and 1/2 cup sugar.
Fold milk mixture into egg whites. Pour into lined cake pan and sprinkle 1/4 cup of remaining graham cracker crumbs on the top and freeze.

title: cherry crunch cobbler(microwave)
directions: Microwave butter in small glass dish about 1 minute or until melted.
Combine pie filling and pineapple in an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix and nuts over fruit.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Microwave, uncovered, 15 to 17 minutes or until bubbly throughout.
Serve warm or chill and serve cold.

title: treebeard's shrimp etouffee
directions: In heavy, 5-quart Dutch oven, melt butter.
Add celery, onions and bell pepper.
Stir occasionally.
Cook until vegetables are soft, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: black bean soup with sausage
directions: Wash and salt beans.
Place in Dutch oven.
Add 6 cups water. Soak overnight or bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add butter or ham bone, carrots, onion, Worcestershire sauce, 1 quart water, bay leaf and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cover.
Cook in very slow oven (200°) for 8 or 9 hours.
Puree 3/4 of the beans and vegetables through a food mill or in processor.
Return to kettle. About 30 minutes before serving, coarsely chop sausage or pepperoni.
Add to soup and allow to simmer until ready to serve. Remove bay leaves.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish each portion with one of the toppings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple (drain juice) over bottom of pan.
Put cherry filling in even layer over pineapple.
Spread dry cake mix over both layers. Spread nuts over next.
Slice margarine thin and put over nuts.
Bake at 350° for 43 to 53 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix well.
Bake in well-buttered dish for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate torte
directions: Mix together pecans, butter and flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: wedding salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside until cool.
Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: chocolate no bake cookies(yields 4 dozen)
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in saucepan; add butter and milk. Bring to a boil; stir constantly for 2 minutes while boiling. Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed and then drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool thoroughly and store in airtight container.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: angel food cake
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until peaks form.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add sugar until stiff peaks form.
In separate bowl, sift together the flour and powdered sugar.
Fold this into the egg white mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes in an ungreased tube pan.

title: noodle ring
directions: Melt
butter,
milk and cheese in saucepan.
Add onion, parsley,
pimentos and bread crumbs.
Stir.
Add a little warm mixture
to
beaten
eggs; slowly add eggs to mixture and cook until
thick.
Fold in cooked noodles. Pour into buttered ring mold
or
an
8 x 12-inch casserole.
Let set at room temperature. Bake
at
for
minutes.
Cool and turn out of mold. Serve with English peas in center of mold.

title: banana pudding
directions: You need a container at least 2 inches deep, about a 10 x 10-inch container.
Start layering wafers then cut bananas into slices roundwise.
Layer them on the wafers.
Do this about 3 times.
Do pudding by directions.
Add on top of layers.
Put in refrigerator; cool at least 1 1/2 hours.
Better if eaten the next day.

title: sugar pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water in a bowl.
Add pecans and mix until all are coated.
Mix in small bowl, sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Dump into nut mixture and stir until all are coated.
Place on buttered cookie sheet and bake at 225° for 1 hour.

title: avocado and mushroom piquant
directions: Mix last 8 ingredients well with avocados; pour over mushrooms.
Chill several hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar and butter; add egg and flavorings.
Blend in flour and dry ingredients; refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Divide dough into 2 rolls before refrigerating.
Roll on floured board 3/16-inch; cut with cookie cutter.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 or 7 minutes.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix 2 beaten eggs into mixture.
Add enough water to make dough-like biscuits.
Drop in hot broth and cook covered for 25 minutes.
Great with stew.

title: lemon delicacy
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and cream.
Add beaten egg yolks, flour, lemon juice and rind.
Add milk and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in greased baking dish; set in pan of hot water.
Bake in slow oven (350°) for 45 minutes.

title: a-maize-ing cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, mix corn, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add oil and beat until well
mixed.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to liquid all at one time and stir until blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 15-inch pan and bake 35 to 45 minutes until tests done.
Can be baked in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Frost with caramel icing.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Combine the above ingredients in large bowl.
Then put dough in a bowl that has been greased with corn oil, turn over so that is on both sides of dough.
Cover with a paper towel.
Leave out of refrigerator for 8 hours.
Dough will rise after 8 hours. Dough will rise after 8 hours.
Punch down dough, and kneed on lightly floured surface.
Separate dough into three parts, kneading each part.
Put dough in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes depending on your oven.
Enjoy!

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter.
Coat chicken in melted butter and roll in bread crumbs.
Brown chicken on both sides and place in greased baking dish.
Cover with spaghetti sauce and cook 40 to 45 minutes.
Take out and cover with cheese.
Place chicken back in oven long enough to melt cheese.
Serve with noodles.

title: pippers cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until fluffy and lemon colored.
Gradually add the boiling water while beating; add and blend well the sugar. Sift flour 3 times with baking powder and add to egg and sugar mixture.
Beat the egg whites stiff and add 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat well.
Fold whites into yolk mixture.
Add flavorings; turn into ungreased angel food pan and bake 30 minutes at 300° and 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not turn pan upside down when done.
Cool on rack before taking out of pan.
Serve with whipped cream or frost.

title: grandma garbers pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, flour, spices, salt, egg yolks and milk. Beat egg whites until slightly stiff.
Fold into pumpkin mixture. Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then turn heat down to 350° and bake until done.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth.
Put in crust; put pie filling on top, any flavor.

title: bacon wrapped scallops
directions: Wrap each piece of scallop with a piece of bacon.
Secure with a wooden toothpick.
Sprinkle with Greek seasonings, lemon juice and pepper.
Place on a rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Broil 5 inches from heat 8 minutes or until bacon is crisp, turning once. Serve immediately.
Makes 40 to 44 appetizers.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: To potatoes, add oleo and sugar. Beat eggs and add all other ingredients. Mix into potatoes. Pour into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Beat for 3 minutes at medium speed.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda.
Add to oil mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and pecans.
Bake in a tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.
Allow to cool before slicing and serving.

title: cream of squash soup
directions: Saute squash (peeled and cubed) in butter with onion and garlic.
Add seasonings.
Cook until soft.
Pour squash mixture into blender with chicken broth and puree.
Pour mixture back into pan and add milk.
Heat to a boil.
Enjoy!

title: country supper soup
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, heat chicken, onion and garlic in butter until onion is transparent.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tanarinie
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion; drain any fat off. Add salt.
Put noodles in a casserole.
Add hamburger and corn. Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Combine beef, water and salt in saucepan. Cover and bring to a boil.
Add cabbage, onions, carrots, celery, green pepper and tomatoes.
Return to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 3 1/2 hours.

title: ham pie with dumplings
directions: Make a single pie crust and set aside.
Make dumplings by mixing Bisquick and milk.
In a saucepan, put ham in 3 cups of water.
Season with lots of black pepper.
Bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Drop dumplings by teaspoons into rapid boiling ham mixture.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes without stirring. Add chopped boiled eggs.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Top with rolled out strips of pie crust just to cover.
Bake at 400° until crust is browned.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Separate head cabbage, boil until thick part is almost tender. Spray casserole dish with non-stick spray. Layer cabbage in bottom, spread some cheese over cabbage, spread sour cream, dot with butter and seasoning. Repeat layers until all ingredients are used holding a little cheese for topping. Cover with foil and bake. Remove foil and spread remaining cheddar cheese on top. Put under broiler until it bubbles. Remove and let set for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all together and freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, toss hot spaghetti with olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine eggs and 1/2 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Stir into spaghetti.

title: pecan sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Press down with a glass dipped in sugar. Sprinkle pecans and decorated sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
I put finely chopped pecans in the dough.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Grind raisins, orange and nuts; set aside.
Sift flour with baking soda and salt.
Add 3/4 cup milk and shortening, mix well. Add 1/2 cup milk and eggs, beaten well.
Stir in orange mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
While warm, add topping.

title: cheese straws
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder and salt into bowl.
Cut in butter
and cheese with pastry blender until crumbly.
Sprinkle water over, mix lightly until pastry holds together.
Roll into a rectangle
12 inches by 12 inches on a lightly floured board. Divide
in	half
lengthwise,
then
cut each one of the halves crosswise into
x
2 inch pieces.
Place on a greased baking sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool on paper towel.

title: green bundles
directions: Using the bacon strips that have been cut in half and with toothpicks, secure 9 or 10 green beans in bundle. Place the bundles in 9 x 13-inch pan and cover with marinade made with brown sugar, melted butter, garlic salt and all other ingredients. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container. Use 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons per cup in hot water.

title: german-style mustard
directions: Soak seed and dry mustard in hot water and half the vinegar at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add egg beaten.
Mix well.
Add melted shortening and hot water.
Mix into flour mixture, then add orange juice until dough is wet but not thin.
Fold in broken nuts and cranberries which have been cut in half.
(I sometimes run through salad grinder.)
Put in regular bread pan greased and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.
When done, take from oven, butter top crust and wrap in wax paper.
Put in refrigerator for 3 hours. Take out and put on new paper.
Store in refrigerator until used.

title: lasagna
directions: Grate Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Mix in bowl the eggs, Parmesan cheese and cottage cheese.
Have noodles boiled and slightly cooled.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, put small amount of oil.
Put layer of lasagna noodles, layer of meat mixture and spoon in 1/2 of egg and cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with 1/2 grated cheese, then repeat from noodles to cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Remove from heat. Add next 8 ingredients.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Top with cheese and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Put all ingredients in boiling cider until done, about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hot peppers in tomato sauce
directions: Remove the seeds from the peppers and cut in pieces.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add peppers and boil 3 minutes longer.
Put in hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook and break the chicken breasts into small pieces.
Mix with stuffing mix and add seasoning.
Saute celery and onion in margarine and add to chicken mixture.
Add soup and broth; mix well.
Stir sour cream in lightly.	Place in a casserole sprayed with Pam.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Last 10 minutes increase to 400° to brown well.

title: one loaf bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add shortening, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar to the hot water.
Let cool and mix with the yeast mixture.
Add flour. Knead to make a compact soft ball.
Cover and let rise until double (about 1 hour).
Work down and let rise until double again.
Work down again and make into loaf.
Let rise until double.
Put in a 300° oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: sausage and egg
directions: Fry sausage.
Drain.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Use 3 slices toast, crumpled on bottom of 9 x 13 x 2 baking dish.
Next use 1/2 sausage over toast.
Cover first layer with cheese.
Repeat toast, sausage and cheese.
Next, pour egg mixture over top. Cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fran's crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Saute onion and pepper in margarine in large saucepan. Add soups, milk, chicken and Ro-Tel to onion and pepper mixture. In a 13X9-inch baking pan, layer starting with corn chips, chicken mixture, cheese; repeat for three layers. Top with cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if the skin is tough.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake potatoes at 425° for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes for another 10 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Put frozen fruit punch into a punch bowl and add the sherbet and whole 2 liter of 7 up.
Stir and add ice.
Serve.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in tube pan or 30 to 40 minutes in 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: mandarin orange and pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle powdered jello over cottage cheese, add drained oranges and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt before adding it.
Roll thin, cut and put in greased pans.
Put filling on each and cover with another cookie.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all together, then add the chocolate chips.
Pour in prepared floured cake pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken in butter and salt.
Debone and chunk meat.
Mix soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, milk and onion.
Crunch chips.
Coat bottom of a large casserole dish with chicken broth.
Layer chips, chicken and sauce until all are used.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: egg pie
directions: Cook in 10-inch pie plate.
Cream butter slightly.
Add sugar and cornstarch.
Add beaten eggs and half and half milk.
Stir in vanilla flavor.
Pour in unbaked crust.
Bake until done.
Can test with straw or bake until cake tester comes out clean.

title: olive lover's salad
directions: In a bowl, combine Ripe and Stuffed Olives, Celery, and Garlic. Drizzle with Oil; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
Yield:
3 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: fruit punch
directions: Freeze maraschino cherries and orange slices (cut in quarters) in ice cubes to float in punch or use fresh strawberries or combination.
Punch can be made ahead of time and fruit, soda and ginger ale added at the last minute.
Makes 25 small punch cups.

title: refried beans
directions: In large skillet, heat bacon drippings.
Add beans, onions, garlic and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until all fat is completely absorbed and beans are hot.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Brown onions, celery and hamburger; drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spread mixture in a baking dish and pour 1 can of cream soup over it. Top with green beans and Tater Tots.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: bean chalupa
directions: Place all ingredients in a heavy kettle or slow cooker.
Cover kettle and simmer about 5 hours or until roast falls apart.
Cook in a slow cooker overnight and all the next day.
Break up roast into bite-sized pieces.
Uncover and cook until thick, about 1/2 hour.
Serve over chips and top with cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, sour cream and more.
Serves 10.
Freezes well.

title: dessert delight
directions: Mix together.
Pat in bottom of dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Should be cooked same as cookie dough (cool crust).

title: turkey enchiladas
directions: Saute onions in oil until wilted; do not brown.
Stir in turkey, sour cream, herbs and spices; stir well to mix.
Place approximately 1/3 cup turkey filling on each tortilla and place a strip of green chili on top.
Roll up and place in oven-proof baking dish, seam side down.
Pour chili sauce over top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes to thoroughly heat through.

title: easy-way deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Place yolks in large plastic bag. Place remaining ingredients in bag with yolks.
Press out air. Close bag and knead until contents are thoroughly blended.
Push contents toward corner.
Snip about 1/2-inch off corner of bag. Squeezing bag gently, fill reserved whites with yolk mixture. Chill to blend flavors.

title: baked chicken(100 portions)
directions: Mix together flour and seasonings.
Roll chicken pieces in it. Put on greased pans.
Sprinkle salad oil on chicken and bake.

title: apricot rolls
directions: Sprinkle with more ground nuts.

title: coconut-pecan layer cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour 3 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch). Beat flour, sugar, shortening, butter, milk, egg yolks and vanilla in a large bowl, using low speed. Scrape bowl occasionally. Beat in egg whites on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally. Stir in pecans and coconut. Pour into pans and bake until a wooden toothpick comes out clean after inserted in the center, usually about 30 to 35 minutes. Frost cake with cream cheese pecan frosting. Garnish with pecan halves, if desired. Store in refrigerator.

title: garbanzo dip
directions: Drain garbanzo beans and wash under cold water.
Place all ingredients in blender or food processor
and blend until smooth. Add more oil or water for desired consistency.

title: strawberry cake roll
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper.
Butter lightly.
Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add vanilla. Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg mixture.
Pour into pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Invert pan onto towel sifted with powdered sugar.
Remove pan and paper.
Roll cake inside towel starting at 10-inch side.
Cool.

title: apple brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350. Melt margarine in microwave or pan. Combine other ingredients and mix with margarine. Pour into greased 8 x 8 inch dish. Bake approximately 40 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken and pour in baking dish. Place chicken breasts on top of rice mixture and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions into thin rounds.
Mix them with salt and ice.
Weight them down.
Leave for 3 to 4 hours; drain. Add the rest of the ingredients and heat. Do not boil.
Pack pickles and liquid into sterilized jars.
Seal.
Enjoy all year long.

title: lemon dill sauce for meats
directions: In a small mixing bowl, stir all ingredients together.
Brush sauce on one side of meat 1 minute before removing from grill. Pass around any remaining sauce.
Great for grilled meat, especially pork chops.
Makes 1/2 cup sauce, enough for 4 to 6 pork chops.

title: tuxedo brownie hugs
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease cookie sheet. Stir mix, syrup package, cocoa, water, oil and eggs until blended. Drop by scant teaspoons and bake 8 minutes. Cool 1 minute. Press a Hug into center. Remove to rack to cool. Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: pennsylvania dutch style green beans
directions: Fry bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon and crumble. Drain all but 1 tablespoon drippings. To that, add the onion and brown slightly.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and dry mustard.
Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Stir that reserved liquid into skillet and cook, stirring, until mixture boils.
Blend in brown sugar and vinegar.
Add green beans and heat thoroughly.
Serve, garnished with the crumbled bacon, to four.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Add powdered sugar to whipped topping and whip well.
Fold in peanut butter.
Pour into crust.
Chill.

title: sand tart cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients, then add the other 4 ingredients. Form into small balls; press down with fork.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beth's "magic" chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken in about 3 quarts water until tender.
Remove from stock; let cool and debone.
Add bouillon cubes and grated carrots to stock; simmer until pasta is tender (crush pasta before adding to pot).
Slice cabbage in 1-inch slices all the way to base; add to pot.
Stir, turn off heat and cover.
Let set for 30 minutes, then serve.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Serve with apple slices.
Sprinkle apple slices with lemon juice or Fruit-Fresh to prevent discoloration.

title: angel food cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish (9-inch square).
Make sauce of the first 5 ingredients; cook over low heat, stirring until thick and clear.
Take from heat; add vanilla and butter. Cool.

title: goulumpus
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain well.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, sugar and oregano.
Cover and simmer while cooking macaroni.
Drain macaroni.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of ground beef mixture, macaroni and cheeses.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: christmas fruit slaw
directions: Toss together cabbage mixture, apples, dried fruit bits and pecans in large mixing bowl.

title: microwave fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from fruit with vanilla pudding and cook until thick in microwave according to directions on box, stirring occasionally.
Cool, then add fruit; add bananas before serving.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and mix with other ingredients in crock-pot. Simmer on low for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally to make sure cheese is melted.

title: lasagna
directions: In large pot, mix first nine ingredients, bring to boil and simmer.
Brown ground chuck (seasoned with salt, garlic powder, etc.) in a large skillet.
Add meat to sauce and simmer for at least 1 1/2 or 2 hours.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring pretty often.
If it gets lumpy, beat with a spoon or beater.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue using whites of the eggs.

title: smothered quail
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter and saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Remove from pan.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and oil; saute birds until brown.
Remove from pan; pour off remaining fat. Add wine; scrape up particles on bottom of skillet.
Add soup, onion, mushrooms and cream; stir until well blended.
Return birds, spooning sauce over.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine whole and cream-style corns and slightly beaten eggs. Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and mustard.
Stir in melted butter and milk.
Pour into greased, 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: easy millionaire pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and chill for at least 1 hour.

title: patrick's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls.
Place on wax paper. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate-dipped pretzel rods
directions: In a microwave-safe cup, microwave white chocolate on Medium for 2 minutes; stir.
Let stand about 1 minute, then stir again until smooth.
Place wire rack over sheet of waxed paper, one end of each pretzel into chocolate.
Immediately sprinkle decorations onto dipped ends of pretzels.
Let dry on wire rack until chocolate is set.

title: oven bake
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, salt and pepper in Dutch oven. Boil noodles according to package directions.
Add noodles, soup, corn and peas to the ground beef.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: miller's delight
directions: Melt margarine in frypan. Clean and wash chicken breasts. Place in frypan.
Lightly brown.
Pour other ingredients in and allow to slowly simmer with lid on about 1 hour. Boil water and pour rice in about 15 minutes and drain.
Place rice on plate and cover with gravy and breasts.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups of the flour, the sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl.
Add water, milk and shortening.
Beat on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl frequently.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute, scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in enough remaining flour, 1 cup at a time, to make dough easy to handle.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of casserole dish.
Add crushed Ritz crackers.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Add chicken.
Top with layer of crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Soften ice cream and Cool Whip and mix together.
Crush Oreo cookies, frosting too.
Add crushed cookies to softened ice cream and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix topping and pudding mix.
Mix
well, then add other ingredients.
Chill well.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Melt the butter in a pan.
Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder and milk until smooth.
Pour batter into bottom of pan.
Pour your favorite fruit filling on top.
Fresh peaches make a delicious pie.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until done.

title: mandarin pork roast
directions: Trim fat from meat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Rub mustard on roast.
Place in large Dutch oven; cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer reaches 170°. Drain oranges, reserving liquid.
Set oranges aside.

title: vegetable pakoras indian snack
directions: *Found in health food stores or Indian stores.

title: one-pan granola
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining.
Toast granola on cookie sheets at 350°, stirring often.
Takes approximately 1/2 hour.
When cooled, add 1/2 cup or more of raisins and/or dates. Store in covered container.
Makes one gallon.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.

title: peachy chicken
directions: Skin chicken; season to taste.
Arrange chicken in pan.
Mix peach preserves and dressing.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn chicken halfway.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or so.
Freeze until needed.
Good for party or company.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients together in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; mix well.
Measure and sift all dry ingredients together into a bowl with wet ingredients.
Grate zucchini and stir into mixture.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Sprinkle chips on top of batter.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Tube pan will take at least 1/2 hour more to bake.
Test for doneness.
Cool in pan for a few minutes before turning out on wire rack.

title: mary's sausage and peppers
directions: Remove sausage from its casing and cut into small pieces.
In a large pan, put olive oil and sausage to brown.
Brown well.
Add peppers, onion and garlic.
Brown and then add tomatoes and Italian seasoning or the herbs listed.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook, covered.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Serve in steak rolls or on top of cooked spaghetti.

title: apple pie
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in unbaked pie shell.

title: sesame green beans
directions: In a saucepan, bring beans and water to boil.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cover and cook for 10 to 15 minutes or until beans are crisp-tender; drain.
Add butter, soy sauce and sesame seeds. Toss to coat.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add ingredients, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: 10 layer salad
directions: Place in layers in large bowl.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: marinated crab claws
directions: Put butter, minced garlic, dill weed and Cajun seasoning in pot. Cook for 5 to 10 minutes. Add melted butter. Pour over cooked crab claws and steam in pot for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beachcomber's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
Drain and cool.
Put in salad bowl with the chopped vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garlic powder is optional.

title: create-a-hot-dip
directions: Place cream cheese in medium glass mixing bowl.
Microwave for about 2 minutes on Roast, or until softened.
Add mayonnaise, onions, parsley and ingredients as specified in one of the variations.
Makes about 2 cups of dip.

title: low calorie strawberry salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cottage cheese and crushed pineapple, then add dry jello, mixing well.
Put in refrigerator several hours before serving.

title: husband's delight
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter and sprinkle flour over the pan, then sprinkle pecans.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes until light brown.
Let cool.

title: cheese and bacon mushrooms
directions: Cook bacon; drain and crumble.
Remove stems from mushrooms, chop finely and place in mixing bowl.
Add bacon, cheese, onion and parsley.
Mix well.
Fill mushroom caps, place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: karmel corn
directions: Put 1 cup granulated sugar in blender, scooping out a hollow in the center with a spoon.
Pour 1 tablespoon dark molasses into the hollow and cover with some of the sugar.
Turn the blender on low speed and stop when molasses is mixed.
Keep this sugar in airtight container in the refrigerator until needed.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt marshmallows with margarine in saucepan over low heat; stir occasionally until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popped corn; toss until well coated. With hands slightly moistened with cold water, form into balls. Decorate with fruit, nuts or candy, if desired.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Add oil, soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add pecans, flour, and apples.
Mix well. Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and serve with ice cream or your special frosting.

title: seafood salad
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Spoon mixture onto lettuce leaves and garnish with lemon wedges, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: date nut balls(great for christmas)
directions: Measure margarine, dates, cherries and sugar into medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes a soft paste.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients very well.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in plastic; chill.
Just before serving, roll ball in nuts or parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Season with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Crush bag of chips and put on bottom of casserole dish. Next, place ground beef on crushed chips, then 3/4 bag of shredded cheese.
Mix soup and salsa together in separate bowl.
Pour soup/salsa mix on top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli.
Cut into small pieces.
(I used just florets.)
Add scallions and raisins.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar for dressing.
Pour over broccoli mixture and refrigerate. (Can be made up to 10 hours before serving.)
Add bacon just before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican chicken legs(microwave)
directions: Rinse 6 chicken legs with cold water.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Put seasoning mix on large plate.
Roll legs in mix. Place on a microwave roasting rack.
Have fat part of leg turned toward outside.
The chicken should be arranged to look like the spokes on a bicycle wheel.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 8 to 11 minutes.
They are done when the juices are clear as the chicken is pierced with a fork.
Sprinkle with cheese; return to microwave for 45 seconds on High.

title: old fashion corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Add evaporated milk and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water and add to egg mixture.
Stir in corn.
Pour into round Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean. Enjoy!
Dot with butter if desired.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook until
thick and pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue; brown.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together in bowl.
Set aside.
In a separate bowl, cream the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients and Ricotta cheese alternately to butter mixture, ending with flour.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: oatmeal cake(easy)
directions: Put oatmeal in boiling water and set aside.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add all ingredients to the oatmeal mixture and stir well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate glaze
directions: Heat chocolate and butter over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Stir in water one teaspoon at a time until glaze is desired consistency.
Glazes one 8 or 9-inch layer.

title: scalloped ham, potatoes and cheese
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put ham in bottom of dish. Top with onion and potatoes, then half of the flour, salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat all ingredients.
Heat milk with butter and rest of flour and pour over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes, then 30 minutes, uncovered, with catsup.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: raisin bars
directions: Cook raisins in water, covered, for 20 minutes.
Cool. Crumble together the sugar, flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and margarine; mix like pie crust.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add raisins.
Mix and spread in greased baking sheet (11 x 17-inch). Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost while warm.

title: lo-cal banana cream pie
directions: In top double boiler, beat eggs with evaporated and low-fat milk.
Heat over hot water, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Sweet 'N Low and vanilla. Toss banana slices in lemon juice and arrange on bottom of pie crust.
Pour filling over bananas.
Refrigerate several hours until set.
(See crust recipe.)

title: cousin patricia's zucchini bread
directions: In bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually beat in oil and sugar.
Add grated zucchini, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder, mixing well.
Gradually blend in flour, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan and bake in moderate oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done and starts to leave sides of pan.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes on a rack.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add flour, gradually, stirring constantly until dark brown.
Add white onion and cook until wilted.
Add other veggies and cook until tender on medium heat. Add pureed tomatoes and spices to taste.
Simmer 30 to 45 minutes. Add shrimp 20 to 30 minutes more.
Serve over warm rice.

title: seafood cheesecake
directions: Mix crumbled crackers and melted margarine.
Press into spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cream cheese, eggs and 1/4 cup sour cream.
Add prepared salmon, lemon juice, onion and pepper.
Mix and pour over prepared crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Run knife around outside of pan.
Cool.
Remove sides.
Spread remaining sour cream over top.

title: sausage-cheese quiche
directions: Bake shells and cool.
Cook sausage and drain.
Combine sausage with next 7 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into shells; top with cheese.
Combine milk and eggs, beating just until foamy. Pour evenly over cheese; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes until cheese is lightly brown and quiche is set.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch cubes.
Dip in beaten egg, then in mixture of cornstarch, flour and salt.
Fry in about 1 tablespoon canola or soy oil (make sure oil is very hot).
Turn pork as each piece browns, about 10 minutes.
Add sweet and sour sauce; cover and simmer for 5 minutes, or until sauce is hot and starts to bubble.
Serve over rice.

title: tom thumb cookie bars
directions: Combine Spry and salt.
Add sugar and cream thoroughly.
Add flour and blend.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Pack mixture with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until delicately browned.

title: baked ham and rice
directions: Remove wrapping from ham and rinse.
Trim if needed.
Place in roaster and cover.
Place in preheated oven (500°) for 1 hour. Reduce heat to 250° and continue baking for 2 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven and pour rice around ham and mix in broth.
Cover and return to oven for maybe 45 minutes or until rice is done.
Slice ham and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix cans of juice together.
Add Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add water to make 1 gallon.
Freeze a portion in a ring or favorite design.
Let it float on top of the punch in punch bowl.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Mix fat and sugar in a bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients and mix.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake on bottom rack for about 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: cocoa pie
directions: Cook all ingredients on low heat until thick.
Put in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue frosting.

title: alaska salmon chowder
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving liquid.
Saute onions, celery and garlic in margarine.
Add potatoes, carrots, reserved salmon liquid, chicken broth and seasonings.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until vegetables are nearly tender.
Add broccoli and cook 5 minutes.
Add flaked salmon, evaporated milk and corn; heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with minced parsley to serve.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Note:
If you like, you can use 7-Up instead of orange.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Drain green beans, reserving 1 cup liquid.
In large skillet, cook celery and mushrooms in oil until celery is crisp-tender. Combine reserved liquid from beans with cornstarch, bouillon cube and soy sauce.
Add beans; cook and stir until mixture thickens and boils.
Stir in almonds and serve.
Makes 10 servings.

title: apple fritters
directions: Peel and chop apples; set aside.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add to apples.
Add melted shortening and egg.
Mix well and fry like pancakes on low heat in shortening. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Precook peppers in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes and drain.
Cook ground beef and onion until lightly browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender.
Stir in cheese.
Stuff peppers; stand upright in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rich chocolate fudge
directions: Boil in large pan the sugar, milk and marshmallows for 10 minutes.
Stir continually to keep from sticking.
Remove from heat and beat in margarine, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour in a large, buttered pan; cool and cut in squares.
Store in cool place or refrigerator.

title: fresh lemon ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix thoroughly in blender.
Use 1 teaspoon per cup of hot water.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and granulated sugar.
Beat in vanilla and flour. By hand, stir in chips.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
When cool, sift powdered sugar over top of cookies.

title: french onion soup
directions: Fry onions in butter until light brown.
Add consomme and cook for 20 minutes.
Place toast in a bowl; pour in soup and sprinkle with cheese.

title: vegetable and chicken pot pie
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Add celery and stir over medium-high heat until crisp-tender.
Stir in soup, milk, onion powder, thyme and pepper; mix well.
Stir in vegetables and chicken; heat through.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Place in Dutch oven with ham bone and water. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until beans are tender, 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Remove ham bone and meat.
Cool until it can be handled.
Chop meat and return to soup along with remaining ingredients.
Discard bone.
Simmer 30 minutes or more until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Add water if it gets too dry.

title: fruit nut pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine together.
Add all other ingredients. Mix and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni as package directs; drain.
Meanwhile, prepare seasoning mix with ground turkey, tomato paste, tomato sauce and 1 cup water.

title: cheese, bacon and onion quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain; place in pie shell.
Saute onion in bacon fat until browned.
Drain fat. Stir in eggs, milk, cream, cheese and seasonings.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Serve warm.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar well. Add beaten eggs. Add flour alternately with buttermilk.
Add soda in buttermilk.
Add flavoring.
Pour in prepared 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, debone and dice chicken breasts.
Mix the soup, milk and chicken broth.
Pour 1/3 of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add Chinese noodles, chicken, onion and celery.
Pour rest of soup mixture over top and cover with corn flake crumbs.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish.
Rinse peppers; cut a thin slice from the stem end of each pepper and remove inner white fiber and seeds.
Rinse cavity.
Drop peppers into boiling salted water. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes; remove and set aside to drain. Brown ground beef in oil.
Stir in parsley, salt, pepper and cooked rice.
Lightly fill pepper shells with mixture, heaping slightly. Place on baking dish.
Combine tomatoes, onions, salt, water and pepper; mix well.
Pour over peppers.
Place strips of cheese on top of each pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple syrup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer till jelly has melted and syrup is slightly thickened.
Serve over pancakes, waffles or French toast.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Debone and pound breasts until flat.
On each piece, place 1 strip of cheese, 1 strip of ham and 1 teaspoon dressing mix.
Roll up jelly-roll fashion and secure with toothpicks.
Roll in bread crumbs and brown in skillet.
Arrange breasts in baking dish. Stir together the soups and sherry and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Peel and slice potatoes and onions.
In deep baking dish, place ground beef in bottom.
Next put the potatoes and sprinkle a little salt and pepper, then place onions last.
Mix soup with 1 soup can of water and pour over meat, potatoes and onions.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, then water and bouillon.
Cook and stir until thickened and bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup sauce, chicken, 1 cup cheese, chilies and cumin; mix well.
Dip each tortilla into remaining hot sauce to soften.
Fill each with equal portions of chicken mixture.
Roll up.
Arrange in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon remaining sauce over.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave s'mores
directions: For Each S'More:
Top 1 cracker with chocolate candy and marshmallow.
Place on paper towel.
Microwave on High for 10 to 15 seconds, or until marshmallow is softened.
Cover with another cracker; lightly press together.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cool and drain spaghetti.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form a crust in a buttered 10-inch pie plate.
In skillet, cook ground beef, onion and pepper until tender.
Drain; stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and salts.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of spaghetti crust. Fill pie.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press edges of crescent rolls together and bake on a flat cookie sheet for 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Mix Miracle Whip and salad dressing mix together and spread over cooled crescent rolls. Top with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes, peel and grate.
Melt butter and cheese (don't cook).
Take from fire, stir in sour cream and pour over potatoes. Put in buttered pan and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's potato soup
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter until soft.
Boil diced potatoes in water with salt to taste.
Drain most of water off after potatoes are cooked.
Add milk and mash to make desired consistency.
Add onion and celery mixture and pepper to taste. Heat together and serve hot.

title: cheese zucchini soup
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; set aside for garnish. Saute onion and pepper in bacon fat until tender.
Add zucchini, pimiento, water and salt.
Cover; bring to boil.
Turn down to simmer and cook for about 5 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: chicken alexander
directions: Boil chicken in 2 cups water.
When chicken is tender, strain broth and set aside for later use.
Flake chicken.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil; saute garlic and onion.
Add chicken.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add heated creamed corn.
In another casserole, melt butter.
Add flour, then add broth gradually.
Add evaporated milk; bring to a boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sauteed chicken-corn mixture.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Decorate sides of Pyrex dish with mashed potatoes.
Place chicken in center.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed crab
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter or cooking oil.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Stir in the sauteed celery and onion.
You may put in crab shells if you have them.
If not, spray cookie sheet with Pam and form in 1/2 cup patties.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix, by hand, all ingredients.
Put in ungreased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool 2 to 3 hours. Loosen with a knife and turn out of pan.

title: acorn squash with cranberry filling
directions: Cut squash in half.
Turn upside-down in microwave.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove seeds and skin.
Put pulp in 10-inch square greased casserole.
Mix cranberry sauce, honey and allspice in bowl.
Microwave until hot and bubbly, 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour sauce over squash.
Reheat 2 to 3 minutes.
Be sure squash is cooked.

title: ham and vegetables(crock-pot cooking)
directions: Place ingredients in crock-pot in order given.
Cover and cook on high setting for 4 to 6 hours.
Yields 2 to 3 servings, 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: shrimp with snow peas
directions: Peel shrimp.
Combine soy sauce, wine, broth, garlic and cornstarch and set aside.
Heat oil.
Cook shrimp, snow peas, onions and water chestnuts by adding each separately and stirring rapidly for 3 to 4 minutes.
Cook shrimp only until they are pink and the vegetables until they are soft.
Put all ingredients back into the frypan or wok.
Stir and add the soy sauce mixture and water.
Cook until sauce thickens slightly, about 2 to 3 minutes. Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Grate pickle and onion. Put into mayonnaise. Stir and chill.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Beat egg and milk together and add to flour mixture. Blend. Drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth and cook, covered, for 15 minutes.

title: mother's old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Boil peaches until done with sugar added.
Then add 1/2 cup of flour and water already mixed.
Let boil for a minute, then take off stove and set for a few seconds.
Then pour the other 1/2 cup of flour and water over top.
Then sprinkle sugar and 1/2 stick of margarine on top.
Put in oven and cook to brown top layer.

title: macaroni and ricotta
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions in salted water.
Drain, but save 1 cup of the cooking water.
Put drained macaroni back into pot and add Ricotta and lots of pepper.
If too dry, add some of the cooking water.
Serve while hot.

title: quick and easy pineapple pie
directions: Combine pineapple with juice, instant pudding, and sour cream. fill a baked 9-inch pie shell with above mixture and cover. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: macho nacho salad
directions: Crumble and brown beef.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Spread beans in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with beef and sprinkle with chilies. Cover this with cheese and drizzle with taco sauce.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle black olives and chopped green onions over top.
Spoon sour cream on top also.
Add guacamole to top in addition to sour cream, if desired. Serve with corn tortilla chips.
This is a flexible dip that you can add or subtract from as you prefer.

title: punch
directions: You can take some of the punch and put into ice cube trays and freeze.
