When serving, just add the frozen cubes to the punch.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
Pour batter in square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch. In small bowl, combine remaining cocoa, 1/2 cup sugar and brown sugar.
Sprinkle mixture evenly over bottom.
Pour hot water over top; do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Let stand 15 minutes.
Spoon sauce from bottom of pan over top of cake when serving.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Cut in butter until it resembles a coarse cornmeal.

title: noodles with corned beef
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Melt butter and stir in flour.
Add milk.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Stir in horseradish, salt, mustard and pepper.
Add thawed peas and the noodles.
Turn into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Slice corned beef into 6 slices and arrange over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: party meat balls
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch meat balls.
Shake 4 or 5 meat balls at a time in Shake 'N Bake.
Place in ungreased shallow pan.
Bake at 450° for about 5 minutes or until lightly browned; serve on wood picks.

title: quick taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and add your taco seasoning.
Dice up your tomatoes, onion and shred up lettuce.
Put everything out on the table.
To build the salad, first put some corn chips on your plate, some salsa, lettuce, hamburger, tomato, onion, cheese and more salsa.
Eat just as is or you can mix it up.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine softened butter and sour cream. Fold in flour.
Fill greased muffin tins 3/4 full and bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
These may be turned on floured surface and rolled out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Muffins are easier.

title: peanut butter cornflakes
directions: Bring sugar and Karo syrup to a boil.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over cornflakes and stir.
Press into buttered dish or pan.

title: cocoa krispies dainties
directions: Blend corn syrup, peanut butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add 2 cups of the Cocoa Krispies.
Mix until well blended.
Shape firmly into 1 or 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll balls in remaining Cocoa Krispies, pressing lightly into surface.
Let stand in cool place to harden.
Or the balls can be rolled in coconut or powdered sugar.
Yield:
about 32 balls.

title: pineapple-lemon punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, combine first three ingredients. Add ice
cubes; garnish with pineapple slices.
Yield:
32 (6 ounce) servings.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Wash and cut stems out of peppers, discarding any dark seeds. Finely chop peppers and onions.
Add salt and mix well.
Let stand about 3 1/2 hours.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to boiling, stirring frequently.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Put boiling hot into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Process half pints and pints 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
If you choose not to process, leave 1/8-inch headspace, place hot lids on and let jars cool overnight.
Store in refrigerator.
Relish will have a well blended flavor, if you let it stand 4 to 6 weeks.

title: cabbage medley
directions: Boil cabbage; drain and pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Add chopped tomatoes.
Pour soup over the top.
Sprinkle top with crumbs, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: white wine cake
directions: *Use 1/4 cup pecans in bottom of pan and 1/4 cup pecans in batter.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel and thinly slice peaches.
In large bowl, toss peaches with 1/4 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Spoon peach mixture into 5 (8 ounce) ramekins or custard cups.

title: green bean bake
directions: Mix beans, onion and soup and pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Take out of oven, spread canned onions on top and bake for 15 minutes or until onions are brown.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: In glass 8 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish, spread coconut in bottom, then dump pineapple and spread evenly.
Now dump blueberry pie filling and spread evenly.
Now dump the dry cake mix on top and spread evenly.
Lay pats of oleo evenly on top. Bake at 350° until brown or about 25 minutes.

title: country style cabbage rolls
directions: Steam cabbage to loosen leaves. Mix ground beef, onion, salt and uncooked rice. Make small balls and wrap in cabbage leaves. Pour tomato juice in cooker and add the rolls. Bring to a boil. Add tomato sauce and 2 c. water. Cook on medium heat for 45 minutes. Turn heat to low and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: old fashioned walnut bread
directions: Resift
flour
with
sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add egg, shortening,
milk
and
vanilla to dry ingredients.
Stir until moist; add nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato dressing(contains 5 calories per tablespoon.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake well; chill. Shake again just before serving.

title: oven chow mein
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and celery.
Add to the rice, chestnuts and mushroom soup in a 4-quart casserole dish.
Add boiling water and soy sauce.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put 1 cup cheese in casserole and reserve 1/2 cup to melt on top during last 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together; bake until bubbly, 30 to 45 minutes, at 325°.
Use 12 x 7-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: raspberry delight mold
directions: Drain raspberries, reserving liquid. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add reserved liquid and enough cold water to measure 3/4 cup. Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in fruit and miniature marshmallows. Pour into a 2-quart mold. Chill until almost firm. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Cool. Gradually add to mayonnaise, mixing until blended. Fold in whipped cream and pour over molded layer. Chill until firm. Unmold and garnish as desired.

title: frozen roll coffeecake
directions: Lightly grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put pecans in bottom of pan.
Lay rolls (frozen from freezer) over nuts.
Shake 1/2 package of pudding mix over top.
Melt oleo.
Pour over all. Shake cinnamon over all.
Cover with damp cloth and let stand on counter overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Turn out on plate or foil as soon as you remove rolls from oven.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain all fruit.
Mix pistachio and pineapple together first. Then add other ingredients.

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Sprinkle cucumbers with salt.
Let stand for 30 minutes; pat dry with paper towels.
Stir dill into sour cream.
Add cucumbers and mix well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy oven lasagna
directions: Brown beef, drain.
Add water, sauce and salt; bring to a boil.
In 2-quart dish (11 x 7-inch) layer hot sauce, uncooked noodles, cheeses and repeat layers.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting. Garnish with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange cake
directions: Grind raisins and orange rind.
Take the juice of the orange and 1/2 cup brown sugar and mix.
Pour on top of cake when done. Bake in a medium-size loaf pan.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Tear up bread and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle ham and cheeses evenly over bread.
Put beaten eggs, milk, salt, pepper, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce in a bowl and beat thoroughly.
Pour over ham and cheese. Cover overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; cover the last 15 minutes of baking.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Place milk and sugar in large saucepan; mix well and bring to a boil.
Let boil for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In large mixing bowl, add chocolate pieces, chips, margarine and marshmallow cream.
Pour milk mixture over chocolate mixture and stir until blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish or pan.
Chill until firm.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat the yolks until thick and light.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Mix the flour and meal with remaining sugar.
Add the melted butter and milk.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake slowly at 300° until set.
Makes 2 medium pies or 1 large pie.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels, milk and butter in double boiler.
Arrange pecan halves on buttered baking sheet.
Spoon 1 teaspoon caramel mixture over each 4 nuts.
Refrigerate uncovered for 30 minutes. Melt chocolate chips; spoon over each turtle to cover.
Makes 24.

title: grilled kabobs
directions: You will need 8 to 12-inch wooden skewers.

title: spicy sauce
directions: In mixing bowl, combine ingredients.
Serve with green enchiladas.

title: creamed corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
Mix flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Cut in margarine with pastry blender.
In a large measuring cup, mix buttermilk, egg and corn.
Stir into flour mixture just until moist.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden.
Allow to cool on rack for 5 minutes before removing from pans.

title: rice dressing
directions: Boil gizzards, white onions, salt and pepper for 1 1/2 hours. Add livers and boil 30 minutes longer. Cook rice.
Chop onions (white and green).
Chop livers and onions in food processor.
Mix chopped livers and gizzards, rice, onions, broth (2 cups), salt and pepper.
Put a little cooking oil in pot and heat thoroughly.

title: stew
directions: Cook all meat till tender, saving the broth. Take meat off the bone and remove all fat & skin. Pull apart meat. In a large pot put all meat and add enough broth to cover,

plus about 1 quart. Add tomatoes and onions and bring to a boil; add potatoes, Durkees, hot sauce, and ketchup. Reduce heat to simmer and cook for 2 hours, stirring often until most of the liquid is cooked out. Add corn last and cook for 15 minutes, stirring all the time it cooks so it won't stick. This is supposed to be thick, but if it is too thick for you, just add a little more broth.

title: "best" italian salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients and shake well.

title: lime salad
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil, add Jell-O, stir and let cool.
Then add buttermilk, pecans, coconut and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Pour into large bowl and chill.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Let cool.
Add orange juice and 2 bananas, also 5 bananas.
Freeze.
To serve, use equal parts frozen mixture (partly thawed) and 7-Up.
Pour over orange sherbet.
Serves 30 (12 ounce) glasses or 50 punch cups.

title: night-before casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter; place 6 slices in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top each bread slice with a slice of cheese and ham; brush with mustard.
Place the remaining bread slices, buttered side up, over mustard.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Garnish with parsley.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, sifted dry ingredients and flavoring; mix well, then stir in other ingredients.
Drop on well-greased cookie sheet; bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Alternate layers of potatoes, sliced onions, salt and pepper and butter.
Cover with soup mixed with 1/2 can of water.
Cook in a covered dish for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Let vinegar and spices come to a boil. Add tomatoes, onions and all peppers.
Cook 30 minutes.
Seal while hot.

title: manicotti
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Heat Teflon coated crepe size pan to a better than medium heat.
Your batter will be thin. Pour enough in the middle to swirl to a perfect circle.
Crepe should be turned when bubbles appear; do not brown them, they will be light in color.

title: chicken with lime butter
directions: Put lime juice in pan and heat over low heat until juice begins to bubble.
Add butter stirring until butter becomes opaque and forms a thickened sauce.
Stir in chives and dill weed.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: lemon-pecan squares
directions: Combine flour, sugar and 1 teaspoon lemon rind.
Cut butter into this mixture with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press firmly and evenly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over baked layer; set aside.
Combine condensed milk and remaining 2 teaspoons lemon rind.
Drizzle evenly over coconut.
Sprinkle pecans on top, pressing down slightly.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll into balls.
Cook in oven at 350° until done and browned.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Partially cook carrots.
Dice carrots and green pepper.
Add other ingredients.
Allow to stand in refrigerator at least a couple of days.
Lasts for up to 2 weeks.

title: red hot cheese wafers
directions: Melt butter.
Pour over grated cheese; add salt, red pepper and peanuts.
Stir to mix.
Gradually mix in flour.
When thoroughly mixed, form dough into 1-inch logs.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until cold enough to slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake slices on cookie sheet in preheated 475° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: parsley rice
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given, mix well.
Pour into a 9x14-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for about one hour.
Serves about 12.

title: baked fish with mushroom sauce
directions: Unwrap fish fillets and let stand at room temperature for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cut each block into 2 or 3 portions.
Place slightly apart in greased shallow 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole. Stir mushroom soup, instant minced onion, sliced mushrooms, dill weed and sherry or wine.
Spread soup mix over fish.
Bake uncovered at 450° until fish is almost opaque, 22 to 26 minutes. Toss croutons with butter.
Sprinkle over fish and bake about 5 minutes more until croutons are brown.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add slightly beaten egg and rhubarb.
Fill pie with rhubarb mixture, top with oleo.
Apply top pie crust.
Cut holes for vents.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and decrease oven to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: venison back strap and gravy
directions: You will need a large iron "spider."

title: banana yam casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender but firm.
Peel, slice bananas crosswise.
Pour lemon juice over sliced bananas.
Butter a casserole.
Alternate layers of sweet potatoes and bananas. Sprinkle each layer with sugar; dot with butter.
Add pecans to top layer of sugar.
Bake until potatoes and bananas are soft and top of dish is lightly browned.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine saltines and broth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: stewed apples
directions: Cover with water and cook until tender (Check with fork). Take apples out of water and put in bowl.
In water from apples, add sugar to taste and 6 to 8 drops of McCormick's Vanilla, butter and nut flavoring.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Pour over apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: peanut butter cream pie
directions: Cream the powdered sugar and peanut butter mixture until crumbly.
Set aside.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour in greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Powder sugar top if desired.

title: play clay
directions: Blend together baking soda and cornstarch.
Add the water and mix until smooth.
Boil 1 minute to consistency of moist mashed potatoes.
Stir constantly.
Spoon out on plate.
Cover with damp cloth and cool.
Knead and roll out on waxed paper.

title: busby's chili
directions: Cook pepper and onion in cooking oil until tender.
Add deerburger and brown.
Pour off fat.
Combine all other ingredients and 1 cup of water.
Simmer for 45 minutes covered. Serve hot with crackers.

title: most requested chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans and line bottom of pans with waxed paper.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer on low 30 seconds, scraping bowl frequently.
Beat at medium speed an additional 2 minutes.
Will be thin.
Pour evenly into pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Remove waxed paper and cool completely on wire rack.
Ice with fluffy white icing.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and salt.
Chill several hours.
Add celery, grapes, chopped eggs, mayonnaise and almonds; toss lightly.
Season with salt to taste.
Makes 4 to 5 servings on lettuce.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Cream two cream cheeses together.
Spread on bottom of serving plate.
Mix together seafood sauce, horseradish, sugar and ketchup.
Spread on top of cream cheese layer.
Sprinkle shrimp on top.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Grease casserole dish.
Crumble potato chips or Ritz crackers on top.
I use Ritz crackers mixed with 1 cup margarine.
Mash 1 1/2 tubes crackers.
Stir in margarine.
Put on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch or smaller cubes.
In a Dutch oven, add water, beef and bouillon.
Boil until beef is almost tender.
Add onions and potatoes; simmer 30 minutes.
Add spices and bag of vegetables and simmer until they are tender.
(Keep adding water to retain original water level.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, butter and eggs (make sure each is at room temperature).
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Cook at 325° for approximately 2 hours.
Start cake in cold oven, then turn on after you put cake in.

title: freezer cucumber pickles
directions: Place cucumbers, onion and green pepper slices in bowl; sprinkle between layers with salt and allow to stand in refrigerator for at least 2 hours or overnight.
Rinse well and drain.
Prepare solution of sugar and vinegar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mixture may be heated slightly to dissolve sugar. Place cucumber mixture in freezer bags or boxes and pour solution over to cover.
Store in freezer.
Defrost when needed.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix vegetables with Vegetable Supreme.
Add rotelle and mix well.
Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours.
Keeps well.

title: white bean soup with bacon
directions: Note:
Preparation time is 15 minutes.
Cook time is 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients until foamy.
Beat eggs, salt and sugar, then add vanilla and shortening.
Add raisin mixture to egg mixture, then add flour.
Fill 4 (No. 2) cans 2/3 full.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese together in a large bowl and mix until fluffy.
Add sugar; beat until creamy and add all extracts. Add eggs one at a time and flour, alternating.
Put in large tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Put in cold oven.

title: hamburger and macaroni casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with salt until brown.
Drain fat.
Add onion; simmer a few minutes.
Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir 2 to 3 times while baking.
For larger quantity, double recipe.

title: cake pan grease
directions: Cream the shortening until light and fluffy with electric mixer.
Add flour gradually.
Beat until well blended.
Add oil 1 teaspoon at a time beating until it is completely incorporated. Pack into plastic container.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, ginger, nutmeg and allspice.
Mix well.
Stir in the cream, milk, beaten eggs and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well. Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: eggs ortega
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish. Beat eggs, milk and flour.
Layer cheese and chilies in dish.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: overnight pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and continue beating. Fold in graham cracker crumbs and baking soda.
Mix in nuts with spatula and spoon into greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick when inserted comes out dry. Refrigerate overnight.
Top with 4 ounces whipped cream before serving.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Spread the pie filling and the applesauce in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Dump half of the dry cake mix evenly over the fruit and push into the fruit.
Dump the remaining mix evenly.
Cover the mix with thin slices of butter or margarine. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Butter cookie sheet.
In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine sugar and corn syrup.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes. Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes or until light brown.
Stir in margarine and vanilla; blend well. Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes.
(Peanuts should be lightly browned.)
Add baking soda and stir gently until light and foamy. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool 30 minutes; break into pieces (1 pound).

title: sausage and potato casserole
directions: Butter dish.
Put in first four ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Beat next four ingredients; add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over 1st mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Drizzle with tomato sauce and cheese.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Put 1/2 vinegar into blender and add peppers.
Reduce to puree.
(May strain mixture through cheesecloth, if desired.)

title: paste
directions: Mix water and flour together slowly in a saucepan.
Add salt and bring to a boil over low heat.
Stir until thick and glossy.

title: squash puppies
directions: Cut, boil and mash squash like mashed potatoes.
Mix until consistency of hush puppies.
Drop in hot grease and cook until brown.

title: philadelphia soft pretzels
directions: In a small bowl dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/4 cup of the lukewarm water.
In a large bowl, combine flours.
Add the teaspoon salt and stir in remaining 3/4 cup lukewarm water.
Add yeast mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix together; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apricot bar cookies
directions: Filling:
Cook dates, apricots, sugar and juice 5 minutes. Set aside.

title: shrimp croquettes
directions: Defrost shrimp; devein if necessary.
Chop finely (about 2 cups).
Melt 3 tablespoons Crisco.
Blend in flour.
Add milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until very thick and smooth; remove from heat.
Add onion, parsley, lemon juice and seasonings.
Stir in shrimp.
Preheat Crisco for deep frying to 350°.
Shape shrimp mixture into 8 cones, about 1/4 cup for each.
Roll in crumbs. Combine egg with water.
Dip cones in egg mixture; roll in crumbs again.
Deep fry a few croquettes at a time in preheated Crisco until brown and hot, about 3 minutes.
Turn if necessary for even cooking.
Drain on a paper towel.
Keep croquettes hot.
Prepare peas according to package directions.
Spoon creamed peas over croquettes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: key lime cream cheese pie
directions: In large bowl, combine cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk and whipped topping.
Stir in Key lime juice until well blended and mix is thick and smooth.
Immediately pour filling into pie shell; chill about 2 hours.
Can freeze.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Put in onion and saute.
Put in chopped broccoli and cover for 5 to 10 minutes.
Add Milnot, rice, cream of chicken, water, Cheez Whiz, salt and pepper to taste. Bring to boil.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange sherbet punch
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and chill.
Place ice in bowl. Add chilled juices, chunks of sherbet and garnish with orange slices.

title: lemon pie or striped delight
directions: Make a crust of the flour, margarine and nuts.
Press in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 16 to 20 minutes. Cool.

title: cheese balls
directions: Process all until well blended.
Shape into balls the size of large marbles.
Bake at 450° until brownish (10 to 15 minutes). May be frozen.
Yield:
about 50 Cheese Balls.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Flatten each chicken breast with meat mallet to 1/4 inch thickness.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; dredge in flour mixture.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken, cook 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until browned. Remove chicken and drain on paper towels; add lemon juice and lemon slices to pan dripping.
Cook until heated.
Pour lemon mixture over chicken, sprinkle with parsley.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix for 2 minutes on low speed.
Combine flour with remaining ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix for 3 minutes with heavy-duty mixer at medium speed.
Add first mixture and mix well.
Cover and let rise for 3 hours or until doubled.
Punch down, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Knead lightly and with lightly floured hands, shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in 3 round 9-inch pans.
Let rise approximately 2 hours in a warm place.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.
Dough may be stored up to 4 days.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add Butterfinger pieces, dredged in dry ingredients. Chill.

title: four seasons salad mold
directions: Heat soup and juice from asparagus can to boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and cream cheese; stir until dissolved. Add water and mayonnaise; beat or stir until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients; turn into mold or Tupperware container. Garnish on bibb lettuce with white asparagus tips.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Flatten 1 package crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pinch perforations together.
Beat remaining ingredients, including yolk (not egg white) together and spread over crust. Top with second package of rolls. Brush with egg white and bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can also top with sprinkles of nuts or raisins.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of a rectangular pan.
Mix taco seasoning and sour cream and spread this mixture on top of beans.
Next, spread avocado dip and then the black olives.
On top of olives, spread tomatoes, then green onion and last, cheese. Serve with corn chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all
ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put in a greased
casserole	dish.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, bell pepper, onion, pimento, flour, salt and pepper. Beat eggs and add to mixture. Bake in greased baking dish at 325° for 1 hour.

title: brie in pastry with tomato chutney
directions: On floured surface, roll out 1 sheet of pastry and using brie as a guide, cut 1 round the size of the brie.
Halve brie horizontally.
Roll out remaining sheet of pastry. Center bottom half of brie (cut side up) on pastry and spread chutney to within 1/2 inch of brie edge.
Top with remaining half of brie (cut side down).

title: orange coconut cream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Set aside.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla. Beat until smooth; pour in square pan.
Combine the remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake 40 minutes, until middle is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes. Spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan on top.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix oleo, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour and baking powder and add to oleo mixture.
Add milk and coconut. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° in a greased and floured pan.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, water and 3 cups berries in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until mixture thickens and begins to boil.
Cool slightly.
Place remaining 2 cups berries in unbaked pie shell.
Stir lemon juice and butter into cooked mixture.
Spoon over fresh berries.
Cover with top crust.
Fold top edge under bottom crust.
Flute and cut slits.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool to room temperature before serving.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 13 ingredients together and place in 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with fried onion rings that have been crushed. Bake 5 minutes more. Can be doubled or tripled and can be made ahead. Serves 8.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; drop by spatula for marbled effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake until cake springs back, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bar-b-barns ribs
directions: Mix
together
and
bring ingredients to a boil.
Place ribs on
rack
in a 300° oven.
Baste the ribs with the sauce. Bake ribs
for
minutes to 1 hour.
Turn over the ribs and baste the other side.
Bake the ribs for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked omelette
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard and beat well.
Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add sausage, mushrooms, cheese and egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until eggs set in center.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a medium saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in just enough water to make a smooth paste. Beat in egg yolks; add water. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium heat. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat; stir in lemon juice, lemon peel and butter. Pour filling into baked pie crust. Top with meringue; spread to well cover edges. Bake 5 to 10 minutes, until golden brown. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: creme-de-menthes brownies
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour and salt, then add vanilla and sugar.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Baked in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: wassail
directions: Boil water.
Put in crock-pot with spices and steep for 5 minutes.
Add sugar, cider, juices and rum.
Heat and serve. Serves 8 to 10.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Brush unbaked pie crust with egg white before pouring in filling.
Cook for 10 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven to 350° and cook until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken curry
directions: Melt butter over low heat in heavy saucepan.
Saute onion and curry powder in melted butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Cook over low heat until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in
chicken broth and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring
constantly.
Boil one minute.
Add chicken and lemon juice.
Heat.
Serve sauce over cooked rice.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat butter in a 3-quart pan and saute onion in it with oregano, basil and thyme until onion is very soft. Add potatoes, broth and water. Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender, then stir in buttermilk. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together cake mix and Jell-O. Add eggs, cooking oil and blackberry wine. Blend on low speed of electric mixer until moistened. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping the bowl frequently. Pour batter into heavily greased Bundt pan. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven or until toothpick inserted in the middle comes out clean. Let cool before removing cake.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli about 5 minutes and drain well.
Melt margarine in 9-inch pie plate.
In separate bowl, mix all ingredients and add melted margarine in also.
Pour mixture back into pie plate and bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip and spread on pretzels.
Mix well Jell-O and hot water.
Mix chopped berries in Jell-O.
Spread over cheese and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate coconut pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa until well blended.
Add eggs and milk alternately.
Mix well.
Add melted butter, coconut and vanilla flavoring.
Blend well.
Pour mixture into raw pie shells. Sprinkle tops with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes four 9-inch pies.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix as it comes from box with undrained pineapple.
Add marshmallows, almond extract and nuts.
Fold in whipped topping. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: christmas stuffed mushrooms
directions: Trim stems from mushrooms; scoop out the centers and mince fine. Mix the minced mushrooms with rest of ingredients. Stuff into center of each mushroom. Place on cookie sheet and bake in 350 degree oven until brown on top.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and mash.
Mix other ingredients with broccoli. Put in casserole dish; bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with buttered crumbs.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Finely chop the green pepper and onion. Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Make a ball.
Chill.

title: holiday appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk.
Stir in dried beef, onion, green pepper and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in sour cream.
Spoon into 8-inch pie plate or small shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pumpkin puffs
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, pumpkin and milk.
Stir in raisins.
Spray muffin tin with nonstick spray, or use paper liners.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 9 muffins.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat together soup and cheese.
Add gelatin that has just been dissolved in warm water.
(Do not dissolve ahead.) Stir in shrimp, celery, onion and mayonnaise.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic salt and Tabasco sauce.
Chill at least 2 hours in mold sprayed with Pam.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in strips and brown in butter; add flour to meat and stir.
Mix together the ketchup, water, soy sauce, bouillon and pepper and add to meat.
Simmer covered 45 minutes; add onions, sliced, green pepper and sliced mushrooms.
Simmer 45 minutes more. Serve with rice or noodles.

title: onion appetizers
directions: Saute onions in butter in a skillet.
Blend the sour cream, flour, salt, pepper and caraway seed.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in bacon and onions.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until filling is set.
Let stand a few minutes.
Cut into wedges to serve.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: eggnog logs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add nutmeg, egg and extracts.
Mix well.
Stir in flour.
If necessary, chill dough.
Shape dough into 1/2-inch diameter rolls.
Cut each into 3-inch long pieces. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.

title: moussaka spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Add the 1 teaspoon nutmeg to sauce; heat in saucepan.
Mix sauce with cooked spaghetti.
Prepare topping.

title: green salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and food coloring together. Separately mix Dream Whip according to instructions on package. Fold Dream Whip in cream cheese mixture.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Put in serving bowl and refrigerate.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add all cut up ingredients. Mix well.
Put into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Combine milk, Bisquick and sugar.
Pour over melted oleo in a large baking dish and add fruit.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into dish. Layer bananas.
Mix Eagle Brand and lemon juice and pour on top. Add remaining ingredients.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients with electric mixer at medium speed.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: grans vegetable salad
directions: Drain first four ingredients and put in large bowl. Then add carrots and onion. Bring to boil the oil, vinegar, sugar, water, salt and pepper. Cool and pour over vegetables. Best if let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: grated potatoes
directions: Grate potatoes, skin and all, on a medium grater.
Add onion. Melt butter and oil in skillet.
When hot, spread the potatoes to a depth of about 1/4-inch.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat until the bottom is crisp and brown.
Flip over and brown on other side.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cut into quarters and serve.

title: linda's apple pie
directions: My sister, Linda Knight, is the best apple pie maker.
We look forward to arriving in Temple, Texas and seeing a freshly baked pie awaiting.

title: cinnamon pecan muffins(made in food processor)
directions: Add dry ingredients to food processor.
Pulse 3 to 4 times to combine ingredients.
Add pecans and pulse 2 to 3 times to chop. Add remaining ingredients mixing egg, oil and milk before combining.
Pulse 4 to 5 times to mix.
Do not overmix.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Place sausages in a slow cooker. In a bowl, combine the pie filling, pineapple and brown sugar. Pour over sausages. Cover and cook on low for 4 hours. Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: scalloped chicken(healthy heart)
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs and 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Stir in broth, eggs, salt, celery, onion, chicken and mushrooms.
In a saucepan, melt butter; brown remaining cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: charleston meat balls
directions: Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet rolls
directions: In mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, eggs, shortening and half of flour.
Mix with spoon until smooth.
Add enough remaining flour to handle easily; mix with hand.
Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Round up in greased bowl; bring greased side up.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in warm place until double, about 1 1/2 hours.

(If kitchen is cool, place dough on a rack over a bowl of hot water and cover completely with a towel.) Punch down; let rise again until almost double, about 30 minutes. Shape; let rise and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Mix all ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Blend potatoes and syrup until smooth.
Add sugar, milk and eggs, beat well.
Add cinnamon, vanilla, baking powder and biscuit mix.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour into a well-greased 9x13 pan.
Bake at 325 degrees about 1 hour or until done.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together and pour into a graham cracker or baked pie shell.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, mix cans of soups and chicken.
Use an empty can to measure 1 can of rice and 1 can of milk.
Mix in 3/4 can French fried onions.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Pour remainder of French fried onions on top and bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: creme bleu
directions: Combine heavy cream, milk, sugar and salt in medium saucepan. Cook over low heat until sugar is dissolved.

Remove from heat. Soften gelatin in cold water and stir into cream mixture. When gelatin is dissolved, beat in the sour cream with rotary beater or whisk only until thoroughly blended and smooth. Add flavoring and gently fold in blueberries.
Pour mixture into individual molds.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Mix flour, soda and salt alternately with mashed bananas.
Mix lightly, being careful not to overbeat.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: ginger wine
directions: Well brew the ginger and put in pan with thinly peeled oranges, lime and sugar.
Bring to boil and simmer for 30 minutes.
Strain and cool.
Add rosen, juice of lime, juice of orange, yeast and toast.
Leave to ferment for 1 week.
Then strain and bottle. Cover container very tight.
Bottle must have tight corks.

title: crunchy coleslaw
directions: In a small saucepan, heat oil. Stir in contents of noodle seasoning packet and garlic salt; cook for 3 to 4 minutes or until well blended. Meanwhile, crush the noodles and place in bowl. Add coleslaw mix and almonds. Drizzle with oil mixture and toss to coat. Serve immediately. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Grease loaf pan.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and beer.
Stir the mix for five minutes, until it's smooth and bubble free.
If the mix seems dry and hard to stir, splash a little water.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together.
Put into greased baking dish.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cheese bites
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add cheese, beating well.
Combine flour, salt and red pepper; gradually add to cheese mixture, mixing well. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll dough into 3/4-inch balls, and freeze until firm.
Place frozen cheese balls on a baking sheet; bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: ham wrap arounds
directions: Wrap ham slices around broccoli spears and place in shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Heat wine in saucepan. Mix cheese and flour, while stirring, add to wine.
Stir until smooth, then stir in mustard and garlic powder.
Pour sauce over all in dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Toast French bread cubes.
Add to the top of casserole, right before serving.
Oh so good!
You'll love this.

title: stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slit the peppers down the middle and remove the seeds and pith.
Combine tomatoes, onion, cilantro and cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff the peppers with the tomato mixture.
Brush peppers with olive oil and bake for 20 minutes (at 400°).
These can also be grilled.

title: potato wafers
directions: Scrub potatoes well; rub with butter.
Cut, without peeling, in rounds 1/4-inch thick.
Place in generously buttered skillet, flat side down.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; cover.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes or until tender.
Turn slices when brown. Serve garnished with minced parsley.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put rice in casserole dish and sprinkle onion soup mix over the top.
Boil water with stick of oleo and pour over top; bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Sprinkle onion rings over top and put back in oven long enough to heat them.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Mix in zucchini, flour and dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.
Put powdered sugar on them if you wish.

title: karin's cake brownies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in melted chocolate.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn into a 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook the carrots until tender; drain. Add all ingredients and mix well. Put in bowl; cover and let set in refrigerator 24 hours.

title: zucchini-oatmeal bread
directions: About 4 hours before serving or day ahead, preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, mix flour, oats, sugar, brown sugar, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In medium bowl, with fork, beat eggs slightly; stir in salad oil, shredded zucchini, vanilla extract and walnuts. Stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Spoon batter evenly into pan.
Bake bread 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan and finish cooling on wire rack. Makes 12 servings.

title: ham cheesewiches
directions: Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Place a slice of ham and 1/2 slice cheese at one end of each rectangle.
Spread with mustard to taste.
Fold over.
Bring edges of dough together to cover filling.
Fork edges to form seal.
Top with other 1/2 slice cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, onion, olives, pimento, salt and celery seed. In 1-quart pan, combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Bring mixture to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand.

title: low-fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugars, margarine, vanilla and egg white in large bowl.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients except ground beef. Mix well; add ground beef. Mix lightly, but thoroughly. Press into loaf pan. Bake 1 hour. Drain; let stand.

title: turkey chili
directions: In 4 or 6-quart Dutch oven, cook turkey until no longer pink. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion, chili powder, parsley flakes, basil, oregano, black pepper, cinnamon, garlic, green pepper and bay leaf.
(I add some water, about 1 cup).
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered for about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and mix all together, then simmer about 10 minutes more.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/4-inch strips, sprinkle with paprika and let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Brown meat in butter, add garlic and broth, cover and simmer 30 minutes or until meat is tender; stir in onions and green peppers and cook until vegetables are tender.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture and cook until thick (about 2 minutes).
Add tomatoes and stir.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: brunch cheese spread
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 teaspoon juice.
Beat pineapple and juice with remaining ingredients.
Spread over toasted bagels, English muffins or wheat bread.

title: strawberry cream filled cake
directions: Grease and flour two round pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla, eggs and egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in alternately with milk, beating after each addition just until blended, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour into pans and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool layers completely.
Spread about 1/2 cup whipped cream over bottom layer.
Place chopped strawberries on whipped cream.
Top with remaining layer and frost top and sides with whipped cream. Garnish top with strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Provolone, adding desired optional ingredients last.
Spread in greased 8 x 12-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with shredded Provolone.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden and set.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix together at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a prepared tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan for 25 minutes. Remove from pan.
Replace in pan.
Put holes in top of cake with a toothpick and pour glaze over the cake. Let sit for 30 minutes and then turn out to a plate. Store, covered.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients except candy bars.
Melt candy with a little milk.
Then add to mixture.
Pour in freezer (4-quart) and freeze.

title: megan's magic cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Layer with chocolate chips and coconut.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Chill, if desired.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13x9-inch pan. Squeeze the orange, reserving 1/3 cup juice for topping; remove seeds.
In a blender or food processor, grind together orange peel and pulp, raisins and walnuts; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine flour, and remaining cake ingredients and mix at low speed until moistened; then beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Stir in orange-raisin mixture.
Pour batter into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: flautas with avocado dip
directions: Heat on high a cup or two of oil in skillet for deep frying, or use a deep fryer.
When hot, lower it and keep it on medium for later use.
Next, soften tortillas slightly by putting them in the microwave for 1 to 2 minutes.
(Spread them on a paper towel; do not stack them on top of each other.)
Fill each tortilla with 2 tablespoons of the shredded meat; roll it up.
If necessary, use a toothpick to hold it together.
Slowly drop a tortilla roll in the skillet; fry for 2 minutes.
(If oil does not cover entire tortilla roll, flip it and fry the other side for an additional 2 minutes.)
Tortilla roll should be crispy.
Place the tortilla rolls (Flautas, pronounced flou-tas) in the oven to keep them warm while you prepare the dip.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until foamy, add sugar and cream of tartar and beat until very stiff.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon onto foil-lined cookie sheet.
Put in oven, turn oven off and do not open until morning.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk; stir well. Beat eggs with sugar and salt. Add to bread/milk mixture with vanilla and butter.
Pour into an 8 x 12-inch buttered casserole.
Sprinkle raisins on top. They will sink.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick chicken catch-a-tory
directions: Lightly salt chicken and bake in 350° oven until done, 45 minutes to an hour.
Cool enough to remove meat from the bones.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and sugar. Add sour cream, eggs and butter and mix together just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Divide batter among 12 buttered muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and mash. Add cheese, butter, sour cream and green onions. Mix together well. Bake in 9 x 13 dish at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and scallops over noodles
directions: Prepare noodles as package directs.
Keep warm. In a 12-inch skillet, over high heat, cook mushrooms in 1 tablespoon hot oil. Remove mushrooms and set aside.
In the same skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot oil, cook shrimp, scallops, pepper and 1/4 teaspoon salt just until seafood is golden.
Gently turn occasionally.
In measuring cup, mix milk, cornstarch and chicken broth until blended.
Stir into seafood mixture in skillet.
Over high heat, bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Add cooked mushrooms and tomato.
Heat through. Serve over warm noodles.

title: biscuit casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until browned. Drain and add tomato sauce,
salt
and pepper.
Mix well.
Brown biscuits in oven. Place
bottom
halves
of biscuits in a casserole dish. Spoon ground
beef mixture over biscuits, then layer cheese on beef mixture.
Next,
place
top halves of biscuits on cheese. Butter tops and bake in oven until butter and cheese melts.

title: pepperoni heart shaped pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 20 strokes.
Pat dough with hands floured with baking mix into 12-inch heart shape on lightly greased cookie sheet, carefully forming a 1/2-inch rim.
Sprinkle evenly with Parmesan cheese.
Stir oregano and garlic powder into tomato sauce; spoon over Parmesan cheese.
Carefully spread to cover; sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: busy day cake
directions: Place shortening in a mixing bowl.
Sift in dry ingredients. Add egg and 1/2 of milk.
Mix until flour is moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add remaining milk and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes longer.
Bake in greased and lightly floured 9 x 9 x 12-inch baking pans for 25 minutes at 375°.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter, powdered sugar and enough milk to make a runny frosting.
Pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Spray baking sheet with cooking spray.
Arrange balls on sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Turn.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes more.
Serve with tomato sauce or chili-grape jelly sauce (50-50). Freeze leftovers.

title: double fudge saucepan brownies
directions: Cook sugar, butter or margarine and water in medium saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Immediately stir in 1 cup chips, stirring until melted.
Stir in eggs and vanilla until blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cut into bars.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen bars.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar till creamy.
Beat in egg.
Sift flours, baking soda and salt.
Put aside.
Combine bananas and yogurt.
Add dry ingredients alternating with banana mixture to margarine mixture, stirring just enough to combine.
Turn in oiled 9x5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350°F. for 50 to 60 minutes.
cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove.
Finish cooling on rack.

title: sticky buns
directions: Butter Bundt pan well.
Drop balls in pan while frozen. Sprinkle
pudding over rolls and add nuts.
Melt margarine and brown
sugar;
stir
well.
Pour
the
mixture
over rolls and pudding.
Cover
and
let
set
overnight at room temperature. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or longer.
Let set for 15 minutes before turning onto a plate.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla; stir flour, salt and nuts together.
Mix with mixer or hands.
Form 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar again.
Store in airtight container.

title: oven barbecue spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown spareribs in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and spoon over ribs.
(The dry mustard will dissolve easier if mixed with a little water first.)
Cover tightly and bake for 1 3/4 hours.
Remove cover and bake additional 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound the chicken.
Mix the eggs, salt and pepper in a pie plate.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and coat with bread crumbs. Saute chicken until light brown on both sides.
Mix tomato sauce and basil together and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes or until it thickens.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Pour sauce over chicken and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Place Mozzarella cheese over chicken and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: microwave toastey o's
directions: Place sugar and syrup in microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Stir mixture.
Put back in on High for 1 minute.
Add the peanut butter to mixture.
Stir in Cheerios and put in jelly roll pan; let cool. Microwave chocolate chips and butter in measuring cup.
Spread mixture on cooled Cheerios mixture.

title: green goddess dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours. Serve with vegetables.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: meat and vegetable stuffed peppers
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Mix beef with all ingredients but peppers, then stuff peppers with mixture.
Place upright in baking dish; add water.
Cover; bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Sprinkle flour on wax paper.
Place dough on wax paper and roll out.
Cut out with cookie cutters. Place on window screen or hard sheet until hard.
Poke a straw in top of ornament before it hardens.
After it hardens, place yarn through it to hang.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Boil water.
Add next 9 or 10 ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour. Add macaroni.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: lemon chess pie *
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add salt, butter and lemon.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes, or until done.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage (not brown); add celery, onions and bell pepper. Cook until tender.
Add pimentos, soup, milk, salt and rice to mixture.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven; add topping and bake 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and bring to a boil. Place the sweet potatoes, crushed pineapple and raisins in casserole.
Pour syrup over the ingredients in the casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: tupperware rolls
directions: Measure the flour into a large Tupperware bowl.
Make a well in the middle of the flour.
In a separate bowl mix the yeast, sugar, salt, eggs, milk and water.
Pour the mixture into the well.
Do not stir.
Put the lid on tightly, burp, replace.
Let the bowl stand until it burps by itself.
Add the margarine.
Stir all the liquid into the flour.
Seal and let it burp again.
When the lid pops the second time, form the rolls.
Add flour to your hands to avoid the sticky mixture.
Let the rolls rise in the greased pans, at least to twice original size.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375° or bake 1/2 the time and freeze them.

title: old fashion heart warming casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown hot dogs and beef in butter. Add tomatoes, sauce mix, celery and onion.
Boil and turn to simmer for 10 minutes, stirring.
Add noodles.
Put in casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: freda's rosettes
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Heat rosette iron by dipping in hot oil. Dip iron in batter and hold in hot oil until crisp and floats free from
hot iron. Cool. Sprinkle confectioners sugar on rosettes.

title: sugarless carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, honey, eggs and vanilla well.
Add flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Mix in carrots and nuts.
Pour in a greased Bundt pan.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix together pecans, flour and melted margarine.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until brown.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, salt and vanilla, beating until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip; spread over cooled crust and top with pie filling.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat and add taco seasoning according to package instructions.
Mix sour cream and salsa in equal proportions in a container; keep chilled.
Prepare all other ingredients.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Line layer cake pans with wax paper. Bake at 350° until done.

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast in a large bowl.
Add water and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up.
Cover; let rise in warm place.
Cook peppers and onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Grease cookie sheet.
Punch dough down; divide into 3 equal parts.
Roll 2 parts into 8-inch circles and one part into 9-inch circle.
Put 8-inch circle on cookie sheet.
Spread 1/2 of pepper mixture over circle to within 1-inch of edge.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of pepperoni and 1/2 of cheeses.
Top with second 8-inch circle.
Repeat with remaining pepper mixture, pepperoni and cheeses.
Place 9-inch circle on top.
Carefully fold edge under; seal securely.
Cover and let rise in a warm place.
Heat oven to 375°.
Place on lowest rack in oven.
Bake 1 hour.
Cut into wedges while warm.

title: green tomato ketchup
directions: Grind all vegetables together; drain in colander until stops dripping.
Mix in salt, sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Roast chili pods in hot oil.
Peel chili under cold running water.
Remove seeds.
Place in blender with enough water to cover chili pods.
Chop.
Boil chicken breasts, set aside.
Put chili in saucepan, add cream of chicken soup and 1 can of water.
Bring to a boil.
Add garlic, onions and diced chicken.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Layer corn tortillas, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: easy ground beef bake
directions: Press ground beef into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Add salt and pepper or garlic salt to taste.
Add chopped bell pepper; add chopped onion. Add asparagus soup (or celery soup), undiluted.
Put a layer of cheese Tater Tots on top (or some squares of cheese).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: vegetable stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package; drain.
In a large skillet, bring cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, mushrooms, potato, onion, garlic, bouillon cube and 1/2 cup of water to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer vegetables until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Separately, mix together the beef stroganoff mix and water, then add to the vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Stir well.
Serve over noodles.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Heat zucchini and onions in some butter. Simmer 5 minutes. Combine soup, sour cream and carrots in a bowl. Add zucchini mixture to bowl. Put melted butter in a dish.
Sprinkle 3/4 Stove Top on melted butter. Put zucchini mixture on top of stuffing. Sprinkle with remaining Stove Top stuffing. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: burrito roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on tortilla shells; roll up and chill before slicing.
Slice in about 1-inch wedges.

title: paella
directions: Fry chicken
in
butter
until
brown and done.
Remove from pan (save
the
butter
in the pan, saute rice), bone and skin the chicken.
After the rice is golden (with saffron) add enough bouillon to
cover
and
cook
until
done.
Then, in a casserole, take bite size pieces of chicken (simply pull apart with fingers) and
layer
the bottom, then add shrimp, clams, pimentos and pepperoni in layers.
On top of that, put a layer of rice.
Add another
layer,
pour
more bouillon if needed. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deluxe chicken rolls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Unroll crescent rolls and press each triangle shape into rectangle.
Place heaping tablespoon of mixture on crescent and roll and seal.
Rub melted margarine on top of roll.
Sprinkle on cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hawaiian bread
directions: Combine the flour, soda, sugar, salt and nuts in mixing bowl and blend by hand.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well and put in greased dish.
Cover; bake for 25 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Makes 12 1/2 cups.

title: uncooked strawberry jam
directions: Wash and hull berries; crush thoroughly.
Measure 2 1/3 to 2 1/2 cups into large bowl.
Add sugar and nutmeg; mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix pectin and lemon juice.
Add to fruit; stir 3 minutes.
Cover loosely; let stand 2 hours.
Stir; pour into hot jars or freezer containers.
Seal.
Let stand until set, 4 to 5 hours.
Refrigerate up to 3 weeks or freeze up to one year.
Makes 5 half pints.

title: apricot coconut balls
directions: Mix apricots and coconut.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix and shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Let stand.

title: donuts
directions: Mix sugar in warm water and add yeast. Let set for five minutes. Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and add enough flour to make a thick dough. Pour out on a floured board and work in flour. Roll out and cut out donuts. Fry in hot shortening.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and grease large cookie pan. Pop out biscuit dough and pat on the pan like a pizza crust. Cover dough with sausage, potatoes and Cheddar cheese. Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Carefully pour over pizza and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until it sets. Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cook pudding according to recipe.
Pour cooked pudding into bowl.
Add dry cake mix and mix until smooth.
Grease 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Serve cold.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Put in baking dish.
Mix broth and celery soup.
Stir until smooth and pour over chicken.

title: irish creme
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Only good for about 1 week.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb, sugar and water until tender.
Pour hot mixture over gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Add undrained pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: triple lemon treat
directions: Cut margarine into flour until mixture is crumbly.
Press into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip, reserving about 1/3 to smooth over cooled pastry. Combine pudding mix and add milk.
Beat until smooth and thickened.
Add lemon juice.
Spread over cream cheese mixture. Spread reserved Cool Whip over top.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix first four ingredients thoroughly.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill one hour.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Core and seed bell peppers; cut into cubes and put in blender to combine with sugar and vinegar. With blender running, drop in jalapeno pepper and process until pureed. Add cranberries and combine. Transfer to a large saucepan. Add water. Bring to a boil and cook over a medium heat until mixture thickens. Pour into jars. Spread cream cheese on crackers. Add a spoon of the sauce. This will keep indefinitely if sealed and stored properly.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Boil water, add broccoli and salt.
Cook until tender.
Set aside.

title: mashed potato yeast rolls
directions: Prepare potatoes and let cool.	Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm
water;
set
aside.
Take
1 1/2 cups warm water and shortening;
dissolve
in
large bowl.
Add eggs, sugar, salt, yeast and
mix together.
Add flour and knead for 5 minutes on floured
board.
Refrigerate
for
hours.
Roll out and let rise for
3 to 4 hours in warm dry place.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in blender.
Delicious over fresh fruit or green salad.
Yield:
approximately 2 cups.

title: frosting
directions: Mix well and spread on cooled cake.

title: peanut star crunchies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Stir in frosting mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a star into each drop. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown. Cool 2 to 3 minutes. Remove from cookie sheet. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: apple jelly for diabetics
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Spread peanuts in one layer on a cookie sheet.
Heat slowly for 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir peanuts often while heating.
Check on brownness from time to time by removing the skins from a few nuts.

title: orange cow shake
directions: Mix Tang as directed; then add milk and ice cream.
Blend together and pour into serving glasses.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into oiled skillet with corn meal.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown on top at 375°.

title: chocolate chip cookies(without sugar)
directions: Cream butter or margarine until soft.
Add honey, maple syrup and eggs.
Blend.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts, chocolate pieces and vanilla and mix.
Drop by half teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets. Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until lightly browned. Remove to rack to cool completely.
Yields about 10 dozen.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Beat egg and
add milk, mixing well. Wash chicken.
Dip each piece into
milk
mixture.
Roll
each
piece
in
flour seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika.
Fry in oil and butter approximately 7 to 10 minutes per side or until tender.

title: egg salad
directions: Put eggs through an egg slicer, then chop the slices up thoroughly.
Mix the chopped egg with the mayonnaise, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, Lawry's and salt and pepper.
Crumble the bacon into medium-sized bits and mix with other ingredients. Refrigerate and allow to sit for about 4 hours for flavors to blend well.
Serves 4.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, cream of tartar and soda together and add to creamed mixture.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon and place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned, but still soft.
Cookies will puff up at first, then flatten out.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple delight(low calorie)
directions: Mix gelatin and sugar; add water.
Place over boiling water and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add pineapple and fold.
Chill until mixture molds slightly.
Add egg whites. Beat with mixer until mixture holds shape.
Place in mold and chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings, 86 calories per serving.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Add melted butter to bread cubes and toss well. In buttered 9 x 13 casserole, layer the ingredients in the following order: 1/2 bread cubes, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 broccoli, ham, broccoli, cheese and bread cubes. Beat eggs and milk thoroughly with seasonings. Pour over all layers. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until puffy and nicely brown.

title: grape pie
directions: Heat grape
juice.
Mix 1 cup sugar, cornstarch, flour, salt and
eggs.	Slowly	add
water
and
stir.	Add
to juice slowly. Stir
and cook until thickened.
Cool slightly.
Pour filling into pie
shell.
Beat egg whites and remaining sugar until stiff peaks
form.
Spread meringue over filling.
Bake at 325°
until meringue
is
brown.
This	is great served in miniature tart shells with a dot of Cool Whip for garnish.

title: wishing cookies
directions: Stir together the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter or margarine until softened.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, molasses, water and peel; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until well mixed.
Cover and chill about 2 hours, or until easy to handle.
Roll dough 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes, or until done.
Remove and cool.
With a decorating bag and writing tip, pipe on design with Lace Icing.
Makes 100.

title: mincemeat
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Will keep a month.

title: "yaourtopeta" - yogurt cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and eggs for 10 minutes; add yogurt, baking soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Beat for 5 minutes.
Add Cream of Wheat until it disappears.
Pour in greased pan; bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until a golden brown.
Pour cool syrup over cake while warm.
Let stand until cool.
Cut diagonally.

title: pita chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch chunks.
Toss chicken with olive or salad oil, oregano and 1 teaspoon salt.
Peel cucumber; cut lengthwise and scrape out seeds.
Coarsely shred on paper towel. Press to remove liquid.
Mix cucumber, yogurt and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cook chicken (about 5 minutes).
In drippings, cook onions until tender.
Fill pita with cucumber mixture, chicken, onions, lettuce and tomato.

title: blueberry coffeecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well a 9-inch round layer cake pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating by hand just until combined.
Turn into pan.
Sprinkle berries on top, then sprinkle with the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 to 10 minutes.

title: farmer's market salad
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Spread the goat cheese on the focaccia. Drizzle with 4 tablespoons of the olive oil and season with salt and pepper. Put the focaccia on a baking sheet and bake until the cheese begins to melt and the bread is lightly toasted, about 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and set aside.

title: peek-a-boo squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well. Add flour, vanilla and almond extract and mix well.
Spread 2/3 of batter in 9 x 14-inch greased pan.
Spread on filling.
Spoon rest of ingredients over filling here and there.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix all and add milk to fill line.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into firm balls.
(If dumpling does not hold shape, add a little flour.)
Drop into a kettle of boiling water and boil 10 to 12 minutes, depending upon the size.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs, Wesson oil and vanilla.
Mix ingredients on low speed.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Grease 2 loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch). Pour in batter and let set in pans for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: cheese pasta
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, add ground beef and sauce.
Let cook for about 20 minutes.
Boil shells, drain then mix with the beef and sauce, top with sour cream then sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pennsylvania dutch green beans
directions: Brown onion and water chestnuts in hot bacon fat.
Drain beans, saving 1 cup liquid.
Mix liquid with rest of ingredients and add to onion.
Cook and stir until it boils.
Add beans and crumbled bacon.
Heat well. Serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Preheat oven to 375° and bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Let cool.

title: blue cheese dip for vegetables
directions: Blend all ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2
hours.
Thin with vinegar if necessary.
Very good with crisp, raw vegetables.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix together and drop in muffin tin.

title: broccoli casserole with cheese nips
directions: Wash, then steam broccoli (only a few minutes).
Chop broccoli into bite size pieces.
Mix soup and mayonnaise together.
Stir mayonnaise mixture into broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Crunch crackers and place around edges of bowl.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Make a day ahead for better flavor.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 15 to 25 minutes.

title: cajun red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Cover with water and let soak overnight. Add salt pork to beans.
Cook 1 hour.
Stir in all other ingredients, except sausage and rice.
Brown sausage in skillet. Drain grease.
Add to beans and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Stir sugar, water and flour and cook until thick.
Add jello while still hot.
Mix well.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover and put into refrigerator for 4 to 8 hours. Serve plain or with Cool Whip with a whole berry on top of each slice.

title: fried oysters
directions: Beat egg, add milk.
Dip
oysters
in
flour mixed with garlic salt, then in egg
and
milk, then in crackers.
Fry in deep fat, or saute in butter until golden brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients until mixture resembles small peas.
Make a hole in center and add egg, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Turn on to a floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out very thin and cut into desired shapes.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until golden brown.

title: chocolate star cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; stir well.
Shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; place chocolate star on top of each cookie and press down.
Bake for 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until stiff.
Set aside.
Add water, almond extract and yolks.
Beat well with electric mixer.
Add sugar, a little at a time, continuing to beat with mixer.
Stir in flour with a spoon.
Fold beaten whites into yolk mixture.
Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Chill Pet milk until icy cold.
With mixer, beat milk until fluffy.
Mix Jell-O, sugar and hot water; cool.
Mix whipped Pet milk and Jell-O mixture together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: pina colada flip(6 servings)
directions: In advance, combine pineapple juice and coconut cream into bowl.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add pinch of salt and sugar; beat until stiff.
Add chopped pecans and chocolate chips.
Spoon onto cookie sheet.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Put in oven and turn off.
Leave at least 4 to 5 hours.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: In food processor, put cauliflower, broccoli and onion.
Mix well.
In a pouring bowl, add garlic salt and as much mayonnaise as you like.
