Let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: chicken salad
directions: Add first 4 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Mix soup and mayo together and pour over chicken mixture.
Just before serving, add grapes and Chinese noodles.
Serve on lettuce leaves with garnish.

title: ranch-style meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, tomato sauce, egg, salt, pepper, garlic powder, onions and soda crackers together in large mixing bowl with your hands until well mixed.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat meat loaf gently into pan.
With ketchup, make a grid design on top of meat loaf.
Then sprinkle parsley over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: aunt irene's rice and broccoli
directions: Saute onions and celery.
Mix in other ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine; add brown sugar and cook just to first bubble, then take off heat and cool.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture with nuts.
Bake in a 9-inch square pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pineapple supreme cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, well-greased. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix and put in baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Put 2 cups crushed corn flakes on top with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: First
crush
Oreos
and lay aside.
Then cream butter, cream cheese
and
sugar.
In
another bowl, mix milk and pudding; allow to set.
Fold in Cool Whip to pudding, then blend in pudding with
cream
cheese
mixture.
In
the bottom of a flower
pot
or sand bucket, layer cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding,
cookies, pudding and cookies.
For fun, add plastic silk flowers and serve with a shovel or spade.

title: holiday cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set pineapple aside.
Add water to pineapple juice to measure 1 cup.
Stir in lemon juice.
Stir juice mixture into gelatin mixture; chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.

title: maple-nut chiffon cake
directions: Sift flour, granulated sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl; stir in brown sugar.
Make a well in dry ingredients. In this order, add salad oil, egg yolks, water and flavoring. Beat until satin smooth.
Combine egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl.
Beat until they form very stiff peaks (stiffer than for meringue or angel cake).
Pour egg yolk batter in thin stream over entire surface of egg whites, gently folding and cutting down, across, bottom, up the side and over, just until blended.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in ungreased 10-inch tube pan in slow oven (325°) for 55 minutes; increase heat to 350° and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.
Invert pan; let cool thoroughly.
Frost cooled cake with Golden Butter Frosting.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine soup, oleo, milk, salt and pepper.
Place sliced potatoes, onions and mixed ingredients in layers in casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter brownie dessert
directions: Bake a pan of 9 x 13 brownies according to package directions and cool.
Stir together peanut butter, powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 Cool Whip.
Spread over brownies.
Top with another Cool Whip and add chocolate and peanut butter chips, if desired.

title: christine's fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl. Add ice ring.

title: pawnbroker's fish cakes
directions: Mix all together and shape into patties; roll them in bread crumbs.
Saute over low heat about 5 minutes, turning now and then.
These freeze well and are good!

title: wonderfully soft raisin drop cookies
directions: Cook raisins in enough water so you will have 3/4 cup raisin water when done.
Mix sugar, eggs, salt, melted butter, soda, baking powder, vanilla and raisin water.
Fold in raisins and flour.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased and floured cookie sheet. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Ovens vary; check at 8 minutes.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Cook noodles.
Blend soups, sour cream and all ingredients except cheese in bowl.
Spread 1/4 chicken mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Alternate layers of noodles, chicken and cheese two times, ending with cheese.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: avocado salad boats
directions: Carefully scoop avocado from shell and dice meat.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon salad into avocado shells to serve.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp onion dip
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve with assorted fresh vegetables or crackers.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: hearth bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix water, garlic and baking mix to form dough.
Form into a 10-inch circle on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush circle with margarine.
Sprinkle with seeds; press into dough.
Cut circle into 12 wedges.
Bake until golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: connie's russian tea
directions: Mix first four ingredients and add the sugar and boiling water.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate (walnut) pie
directions: Beat the eggs until foamy.
Mix in all other ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
May be served warm or with ice cream or refrigerate.

title: wop mix
directions: Chop all vegetables fine including celery leaves.
Use all juices.
Mix well and refrigerate.
This is great on sandwiches and salads.

title: baked apples
directions: Core apples, leaving small plug in blossom end.
Peel skin 1-inch from top.
Combine sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Fill apples with mixture.
Arrange apples in 8-inch square dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with water.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High for 11 to 13 minutes.
After cooking, release plastic wrap. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled, spooning sauce over apples.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Blend ice cream and pumpkin.
Add pudding mix, cinnamon and spices.
Fold
together as quickly and lightly as possible to prevent
ice
cream
from
becoming
too
soft.
Pour
into prepared baked crust
and chill at least 8 hours or overnight. Garnish with whipped cream before serving.

title: chinese meat skillet
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet; salt.
Cover with celery, onion, pepper, vegetables and potatoes.
Cover all with cabbage.
Mix broth and soy sauce; pour over all.
Cover.
Heat; reduce temperature to low and cook about 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat; sprinkle noodles over the top.

title: individual beef wellington
directions: Brown fillets in unsalted butter, making sure they are brown on all sides.
Remove from skillet and let cool on wire rack. Saute mushrooms in pan drippings.
Flatten the dough from one package of crescent rolls.
Using a cup, cut 8 circles.
Flatten the second package of dough and cut into strips approximately 1 1/2 inches wide.
Place each fillet on a circle and top with 1/4 of the mushrooms and another circle.
Then, using the strips around the sides, carefully seal the steaks by pinching together the edges of the dough circles and the strips.
(This may be done several hours ahead and refrigerated, covered, until 30 minutes before cooking time.)
Mix the beaten egg and milk and brush on all sides of each encased fillet.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve with Madeira sauce.

title: ham and sausage jambalaya from dudley's
directions: Combine tomatoes, seasoning and cut pieces of ham and sausage. Mix cooked rice into mixture with fork.
Add green onions and parsley.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Mix and pour into well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: dough for fried pies
directions: Make dough and cover in bowl.
This will keep in refrigerator at least 2 weeks.

title: diet banana pudding
directions: Beat egg in small saucepan.
Add milk and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened.
Take off burner and add remaining ingredients.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with hand mixer; beat on high.
Pour into plate. Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: frosted tweety cake
directions: In a
large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; add eggs and oil.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in vanilla,
cup
pecans,
bananas
and pineapple.
Pour batter evenly
into
greased
and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake
at
for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in
center
comes out clean.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes before trying to remove.
Invert on wire racks and let cool completely.
Spread Cream Cheese Frosting between layers, around sides
and
on
top;
sprinkle top with 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: nellie muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Cut shortening into dry mixture.
Add milk to make soft dough.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick and spread with butter, then brown sugar. Roll up as for jelly roll; slice.
Place in greased muffin pans. Add 1/2 teaspoon jelly
or jam on top of each muffin. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Prepare noodles as directed.
In 3-quart saucepan, over medium heat, cook celery and onion in oil until tender.
Stir in undiluted soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Drain noodles.
Add tuna and tomato chunks to saucepan and toss to coat.
Spoon mixture into deep 2-quart casserole.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat the eggs with the flour until well beaten.
Add the Eagle Brand milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Any drained fruit (canned) or fresh fruit can be added.
Pour mixture into 1-gallon ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill container about 80% full.
Freeze as usual.

title: lipton onion mushroom meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. In large shallow baking pan, shape into loaf.
Bake 45 minutes or until done.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Preheat oil several inches deep in deep fat fryer or electric skillet to 375°.
Beat eggs; add milk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Stir milk and egg mixture into flour; beat until smooth. Pour mixture into funnel with finger covering hole.
Hold over hot oil and let it swirl into the oil making zigzag motions.
Cook until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: hot french baked potatoes
directions: Rub each potato thoroughly with the 1 tablespoon oil.
Bake until done.
While potatoes cook, whisk remaining ingredients in small bowl until well blended.
Arrange cooked potatoes on platter or plate with rim.
Potatoes must touch bottom.
Make single layer only.
Open each potato by plunging a fork in and twisting.
Pour dressing over all and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cottage cheese rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend cottage cheese, egg, milk and oil in processor or by hand.
Sift together dry ingredients and combine with cottage cheese mixture.
Turn out on a floured board and knead until smooth.
Shape into 8 to 10 rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Brush each roll with the undiluted egg yolk and slash the top with a sharp knife.
Sprinkle the tops with the poppy seed or caraway seed.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes until golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake according to instructions on box.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream of coconut and sweetened milk.
Have it ready to pour over cake when it gets done.
Take a toothpick and punch cake full of holes.
Then put Cool Whip and frozen coconut.

title: hortense's rolls(serves 15)
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; heat to lukewarm.
Let cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar to this mixture.
When cool, mix yeast, eggs and flour (with soda and baking powder already added).
Make out and let rise (about 3 hours in "these air-conditioned houses," Hortense says).
Bake in oven at 400°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Butter standard muffin tins.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening. Add milk and yeast. Roll out dough and cut into desired size. Bake at 450° for 18 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased baking dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: curried chicken
directions: Arrange chicken on top of broccoli in greased large casserole. Combine curry, soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Spread over chicken.
Combine crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Good served with rice.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine and Milnot on medium heat.
When it just starts to boil, time 5 minutes.
Take off heat and stir in peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla. Pour in a buttered pan.
Let cool.
Cut in squares.

title: pecan praline sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients over medium heat, stirring often, until thickened. Serve immediately over ice cream or dessert of your choice.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease bottom of muffin pan.
Can use paper baking cups.
Beat egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except for blueberries, until good and moist.
Add blueberries. Spoon batter evenly into cups.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, vanilla, butter and egg.
Beat together for 10 minutes.
Spread mixture in bottom of crust.
Peel and slice bananas.
Place on creamed layer.
Spread pineapple over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Chill for 4 hours.

title: grandma's blue ribbon banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Next, add sour milk followed by the dry ingredients.
Roll nuts in a little flour, and add to batter.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add bananas.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Increase to 350° and bake for 20 more minutes, or until done in center.
When cool, frost with butter cream frosting.

title: carrot ginger fish
directions: Spray nonstick pan with Pam on medium-high heat.
Lightly brown fish on both sides (approximately 1 minute each side).
Add carrot juice and ginger juice; let fish poach for 5 to 10 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Garnish with paprika.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Place in a covered dish and refrigerate.

title: stoup
directions: Cut beef into bite-sized pieces and cook in soup kettle until brown.
Cover meat with bouillon and add onion, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, bay leaves and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer an hour.
Add carrots and cook 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and corn. Simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: ranch beans
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° 1 1/2 hours.

title: valerie's gingerbread men
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Chill the dough.
It is easier to handle if the dough is divided into 4 pieces and then chill wrapped in wax paper.
Roll the dough out to a thickness of about 1/4-inch on a well floured board.
Use cookie cutters to make gingerbread men or other shapes.
Bake in a preheated oven to 350° for 8 to 15 minutes.
Cookies are done when they begin to turn deep brown.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Place the cream cheese in a bowl and cream well until soft and smooth.
Combine milk and lemon juice.
Then gradually add to cream cheese.
Fold in sour cream.
Place small cups and refrigerate garnish with cherry pie filling and sprinkle mixture of graham cracker crumbs and butter.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix together until soft dough forms.

After beating, if dough is too sticky, gradually mix in enough Bisquick (up to 1/4 cup) to make dough easy to handle. Turn onto surface dusted with Bisquick. Gently roll in baking mix to coat. Shape into ball. Knead. Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutters dipped in baking mix. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 8 to 10 minutes. Bake at 450°.

title: bo's cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add Cheddar cheese and mix.
Next, add bacon bits and onion powder.
Mix.
Let chill about 30 minutes and shape into a ball.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: new orleans chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in 2-quart shallow casserole.
Pour mixture over; cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
May uncover last 15 to 20 minutes.
Leftovers reheat or good frozen.
To salt chicken, may first soak in water and 1 tablespoon salt to cover for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: basil chicken
directions: In a medium skillet, cook scallions and garlic in olive oil until soft, about 2 minutes.
Add chicken, stirring until cooked through.
Add basil, salt, pepper and red pepper flakes.
Toss with 12 ounces cooked linguini, parsley, Parmesan cheese and margarine.

title: caramelized chex mix
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Melt the rest of ingredients in pan.
Bring to a boil; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Pour over cereal mix.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.

title: easy pizza
directions: Spread bread on pizza pan.
Add spices to tomato sauce and paste.
Spread on bread.
Add browned sausage, olives, sauteed mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: frozen pie
directions: Mix and pour into small graham cracker crust.
Freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, stir well and pour into serving bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: byrl's blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, blackberries and sour cream.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, nutmeg, allspice, cloves and salt.	Add dry ingredients
to
the first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Jif, Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork. Bake one sheet at a time for 7 to 8 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes on sheet.
Remove and place on foil on counter.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first three ingredients. Spread on cookie sheet and bake 375° for 4-6 minutes; watch closely. Let cool. Mix cream cheese and sugar; add pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and chill. Just before serving, fold in pretzel mixture.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add apples. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mocha frosting
directions: Over low heat, mix chocolate, coffee powder and water in small saucepan until smooth.
Set aside for cooling.
Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat in cooled chocolate mixture, then beat in confectioners sugar. Refrigerate frosting until thick enough to spread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add Tang and pudding mix.
Pour juice over this.
Mix all together.
Let set for a couple of hours.

title: pink salad
directions: Whip Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together; add all other ingredients.

title: rosanna ouellette's sweet cherries
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Beat in coconut, cream and almond extract.
Drain cherries.
Cover each cherry with a small amount of the coconut mixture to about 1/4-inch.
Roll the balls in graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In casserole dish, layer half of asparagus, 1 can of soup, 2 eggs and salt and pepper to taste.
Layer half of crackers. Repeat layers.
Bake at 450° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Heat oil in heavy large pot over high heat. Working in batches, add chicken and cook until brown on all sides, about 8 minutes per batch. Transfer chicken to platter. Reduce heat to medium-high; add onion, bell peppers, parsley and garlic to pot. Saute until onions are tender, about 5 minutes. Add sausage, bay leaves, chili powder, thyme, cayenne pepper and cloves; saute until spices are fragrant and flavors blend, about 5 minutes. Add rice; stir to coat.

title: devilicious ham spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and deviled ham in bowl; mix well.
Add relish, mustard, salt and pepper; mix well.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with party rye bread or crackers.
Yields 16 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut
eggplant
crosswise into 1/2 inch slices; sprinkle with salt.
Let	stand
minutes;
rinse
and
drain.
Dip eggplant in	mixture of egg, water, oregano, salt and pepper. Saute in
oil until
brown,
about 8 minutes.
Spread 3/4 cup Italian
Sauce in	a 13 x9-inch baking pan;
arrange eggplant over
sauce. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese; spoon remaining sauce
over. Sprinkle
with
Parmesan
cheese.
Bake
at 350° until eggplant is tender, about 20 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs. Reserve 1 cup of crumbs. Slice bananas and layer over crumbs. Slice frozen ice cream in 1/2-inch slices and lay over bananas. Sprinkle nuts over ice cream and until firm. You can save some nuts to sprinkle on top also.

title: lazy day salad
directions: In a large bowl mix together by hand, fruit cocktail, oranges, pineapple & juice and pudding mixes. Fold in large container cool whip and refrigerate for 2 hours. Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: scotch shortbread(rolled cookie)
directions: Mix butter and sugar thoroughly, then gradually add flour, working with hands. Chill dough.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix together yeast, sugar and lukewarm water.
In small bowl mix self-rising flour and Crisco.
In another bowl mix buttermilk and soda.
Mix yeats and buttermilk mixture.
Add flour mixture. Beat well with large spoon.
Cover and let rise in refrigerator. Use as needed.
(Do not knead this.)
Dip out by tablespoon into Crisco greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: baked fruit
directions: Drain fruit and place in 3-quart casserole.
Add drained cherries on top of fruit.
Melt butter and add sugar and curry powder.
Pour over fruit and bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: frosting for pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and frost cooled pumpkin cake.

title: meat loaf
directions: Make loaf what your one hand can hold.
Roll in flour and brown.
Put in roaster pan.
Make gravy with one glass water, 1/2 can beef broth, 2 teaspoons flour and 1 tablespoon Kitchen Bouquet. Mix together.
Pour over meat loaf.
Cook 1 hour in the oven at 350°.
You can use tomato for the gravy.

title: best brownies
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs; using a wooden spoon, beat well.
In a small bowl, mix next 4 ingredients. Gradually blend into egg mixture.
Stir in nuts, if desired. Spread into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli in salt water.
In saucepan, melt butter.
Then blend in flour and cheese.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until the mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in broccoli.
Place in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chunky tomato soup
directions: Cook and crumble bacon; saute onion and set aside.
Combine soup, milk, tomatoes, basil, oregano and pepper all in the cold state so mixture will not separate.
Add bacon and bay leaf. Heat on medium, stirring so bottom won't stick.
Serves 2.

title: garden vegetable soup
directions: Saute carrot, onion and garlic in a large saucepan coated with cooking spray until softened. Add broth, cabbage, beans, tomato paste, basil, oregano and salt. Bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer until beans are tender, about 15 minutes. Stir in zucchini and heat 3 to 4 minutes. Serve hot.

title: tropic slush
directions: Mix and freeze in 5-quart container (ice cream pails are ideal).
Stir occasionally to keep blended.
When serving, scoop into glass, then fill up with favorite soft drink: 7-Up, ginger ale or whatever you like.
This is wonderful made the day before a party.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix first two ingredients together and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next three ingredients and beat with mixer for 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Add a layer of bananas, a large can of crushed pineapple (drained) and 1 (8 ounce) container Cool Whip.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugars, beat in eggs and syrup. Sift dry ingredients and add with milk. Bake at 350° until done to touch. It fills about an 8-inch square pan, greased and floured.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix margarine.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients. Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 3-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and let set in oven for 5 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: honey rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and rum.
Mixture should be stiff.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Allow to stand for 24 hours.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Add salt, vanilla and coloring. Pour over corn flakes.
Drop by spoon onto waxed paper.
Decorate with red candies.
Let set 24 hours.

title: michael's favorite chocolate mint cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry
bacon
and
remove
from	grease.
Saute	onions, celery,
bell pepper and garlic in bacon grease.
Add mushroom soup and
Ro-Tel tomatoes to this.	Pour in a large baking pan including
fried bacon.
Saute ground meat and pour Ragu sauce and beef broth to this.
Mix everything including cabbage and raw rice;
season to
taste.
Bake
at	350° covered for about 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and
stir top with bread crumbs and bake another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.
Serve with salad.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Brown beef and add onions.
Add next 10 ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and spinach.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and layer ingredients as follows: noodles, half of meat sauce, noodles, cheese and spinach mixture and remainder of sauce.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: spinach cabrini
directions: Cook spaghetti. In large bowl, mix remaining ingredients together. Add spaghetti; mix well. Place mixture in a 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 minutes and 5 to 10 minutes, uncovered. Slice and serve.

title: green vegetable casserole
directions: Cook limas and broccoli together according to package directions and drain.
Mix sour cream, water chestnuts and soups together; combine with vegetables and put in casserole dish.
Top with Rice Krispies which have been mixed with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl; mix until well blended, about 3 minutes. Scrape sides occasionally.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in "cold" oven.
Set temperature at 325° and bake for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven; cool in pan 5 minutes.
Run knife around sides and remove to cake plate.
Top can be dusted with 10x sugar or iced with favorite frosting.

title: onions with worcestershire
directions: Peel and core onions.
Fill hole with Worcestershire sauce. Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Delicious with grilled chicken or pork.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix well the oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and fold in 1/2 to 1 1/2 cups chopped pecans.
Add in chopped raw apples. Bake at 350° in a tube pan for 1 hour or until done.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage, simmer in a little water.
When cooked, drain and reserve liquid.
Brown meat with onion, garlic and celery for 10 minutes, drain.
Add tomatoes, seasonings and rice.
Mix well. In an oblong casserole bowl or pan, layer cabbage, then meat. Pour liquid over top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: recipe for a wonderful day
directions: Sprinkle unselfishness and patience with teamwork.
Add plenty of industry.
Lighten with good spirits.
Sweeten with a pinch of kindness.
Add a scoop of smiles as thick as figs and raisins in plum puddin'.
Bake by the warmth which "steams" from a big loving heart.

title: rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring water to boil.
Stir in rice and salt.
Cover and simmer until all water is absorbed, approximately 30 minutes.
Add milk and boil gently, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens slightly, about 5 minutes.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Gradually stir in rice mixture; mix well. Stir in raisins and sprinkle nutmeg and cinnamon over top.
Place casserole in a pan containing about 1 inch hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.
Add toppings of choice (fruit, icing, preserves).

title: diane and bob potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook (boil) until done.
Mash using 1/3 stick butter, sour cream and enough milk to make them smooth.
Keep warm. Dice onion and celery.
In frying pan melt remaining butter.
Add thyme, salt, pepper, onion and celery.
Saute until transparent. Add cooked vegetables to potatoes.
Then add grated cheese and croutons.
Mix. Heat thoroughly in oven (375°) for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serve hot.
Great plain or with gravy.

title: lemon rice stuffed sole
directions: Cook celery and onion in 1 tablespoon butter in medium skillet until tender.
Stir in rice, lemon peel, salt substitute, thyme, pepper and lemon juice.
Place fillets in buttered shallow baking dish.
Spoon rice mixture on lower portion of each fillet.
Fold over to enclose rice mixture; fasten with wooden picks.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter.
Brush fish with melted butter; sprinkle with parsley.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serves 4.

title: corn, beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add other ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, covered.
Serves 10.

title: potato pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add all other ingredients as they are listed. Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake until firm or pie crust is brown, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Place in a baking dish.
Stir thoroughly.
Bake covered for 45 minutes at 350°.
Fluff with a fork and bake 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: ice cream sandwich cake
directions: Dip ice cream sandwiches in milk.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread Cool Whip over sandwiches.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup. Put nuts on top and freeze.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Rinse potatoes, sliced thoroughly; dry.
Brush 1 tablespoon butter onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Toss potatoes with remaining butter. Arrange a layer of potatoes on bottom and sides of pie plate; sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: beef casserole with corn muffin top
directions: Saute beef and onion in the hot fat in a heavy skillet.
Stir in the consomme, parsley, salt, pepper and A.1. Worcestershire sauce.
Spread the mixture in a casserole of a size that will leave at least an inch of space at the top.
Make your favorite muffin recipe or use a corn muffin mix.
Spoon it carefully on top of the casserole, smoothing with a knife.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Serves 5 to 6. Serve with fluffy mashed potatoes and buttered broccoli.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender combine ingredients.
Cover and store in fridge.

title: june's frozen yogurt salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add cold water. With mixer on low speed, beat cream cheese into jello until smooth. Gradually add frozen yogurt and beat until smooth.
Stir in pineapple and strawberries.
Pour mixture into 9 x 13-inch container.
Garnish with nuts and maraschino cherries (if desired). Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve immediately.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Sift
together	flour, salt and baking powder; beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; add water and beat until light
and fluffy.
Gradually
beat
in
sugar;
fold
in dry ingredients
a little
at a time.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not
dry.
Fold into
egg-yolk
batter; add vanilla.
Bake in 10-inch
ungreased tube
pan in slow oven at 325° for about 1 hour.
Invert
pan
to cool cake.	Dust top with confectioners sugar.

title: rigatoni with mushroom sauce
directions: Cook the rigatoni.
In a large frypan, heat oil and saute the garlic, onion and mushrooms about 5 minutes. Add the rest of the ingredients, except cheese.
Let simmer for 15 minutes over medium heat. Stir occasionally. Drain rigatoni.
Toss with sauce and cheese.

title: frozen strawberry-banana dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Pour into a 9-inch square pan.
(Spray with pan spray first.)
Freeze until firm. Cut into squares.
Serves 6 to 9, depending on serving size.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Saute onion in butter in heavy frypan until tender.
Add paprika and mix well.
Add chicken and seasonings.
Cover; cook slowly 1/2 hour.
Turn pieces over and cook until chicken is done. Remove chicken.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Stir up with hands; set one hour.
Melt chocolate candy dips. Dip coconut balls in chocolate.

title: d's chili
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Saute onion with ground beef. Mix all ingredients in a pot. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: parsley buttered carrots
directions: Place butter in 1-quart casserole.
Heat on Full power in microwave for 30 to 60 seconds or until melted.
Stir in carrots and parsley flakes; mix well.
Cook, covered, on Full power for 4 to 6 1/2 minutes or until tender.

title: rolls
directions: Stir until well mixed.
Do not beat.
Grease muffin pans. Fill.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: spiced figs
directions: Remove outer layer of skin from figs; place in stone jar or bowl.
Boil other ingredients together for 10 minutes and pour over figs.
Cover and let stand overnight.
In the morning, drain off liquid and bring to boil.
Add figs and cook until tender. Pack into hot jars.
Cover with syrup and seal immediately.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and brown sugar; spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Do not overbake!
Cool for 15 to 20 minutes.
Whip the cream cheese and granulated sugar together, then fold in Cool Whip. Spread over cooled pretzel crust, making sure to cover all pretzel crust evenly.
Mix jello and water until dissolved, then add strawberries and cool until mixture begins to set.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cream together powdered sugar and cream cheese; add Cool Whip.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling mix (I sometimes use 2 cans).
Refrigerate.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix seasoning with sour cream.
Spread on pizza pan.
Top with vegetables and cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Simmer in crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: grandma fawn's pie crust(never fails)
directions: Mix the dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with pastry cutter to a fine crumb stage.
Beat egg, vinegar and water. Add to crumb mixture.
Mix and roll as needed.
Makes 4 large single crust or 2 double crust pies.

title: georgia cookies
directions: Mix together in 2-quart pan the shortening, sugar and milk. Put over medium heat and stir until it reaches a full rolling boil.
Mix together in a large bowl the oats, vanilla, coconut and chocolate chips.
Pour boiling liquid over the dry ingredients and mix together quickly.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press ground beef mixed with next 3 ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with Tater Tots.
Cook for 1 hour at 375°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix 2 cups sugar, oil and eggs; beat well until blended.
Add apples and mix on low speed remaining ingredients and beat until mixture is well blended and all flour is mixed in.
Stir in 1 cup of raisins and 1/2 cup chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or whipped cream or top with apple slices when baking.

title: orange puffy pudding
directions: Mix together, refrigerate, then serve.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into 1-quart greased casserole.
Break 1 package saltine crackers and mix with 3/4 stick margarine (melted) and enough milk or cream to moisten. Place on top of casserole and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creamy garlic dressing(healthful eating)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill.

title: easy cream cheese icing
directions: Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in other 3 ingredients. Spread over cooled cake.

title: corn bread crust
directions: In small bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until mixture is coarse.
In small bowl, combine milk, parsley and egg. Add to dry ingredients; stir to moisten.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until bubbly.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well beaten eggs.
Add spices. Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add to mixture.
Add flour, jam, raisins, coconut, nuts and vanilla; beat well.
Turn into 3 large greased layer pans.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple rings with maple syrup
directions: In a shallow bowl, combine flour, egg, syrup and buttermilk. Dip apple rings on both sides into batter. In an electric skillet or deep-fat fryer, heat 2-inches oil to 375°. Fry apple rings a few at a time, until golden brown, about 2 minutes. Drain on paper towel; dust with confectioners sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with seasonings.
Add onion and bell pepper. Peel potatoes and slice very thin.
Grease deep casserole dish. Drain meat mixture.
Place layer of potatoes on bottom of dish. Add layer of sour cream.
Alternate layers until dish is full. Top with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour half of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: In a pie plate, spread beans; set aside.
Mix together beans, taco seasoning, mayonnaise and onion salt.
Spread this mixture on top of beans.
Spread black olives and top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.
Serve with chips and jalapeno peppers.

title: rouladen(steak rolls)
directions: Take a fairly thin round steak and beat well with a meat cleaver.
Cut into pieces approximately 2 1/2 x 6-inches.
Spread mustard on one side of each piece.
Put a long piece of dill pickle on each piece.
Roll up and wrap with a piece of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Brown on low heat in skillet along with small, cut up onion.
Add some tomato paste and hot water.
Cover and simmer until done.
You may thicken gravy with flour if you like.
Serve with rice.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and drain.
Dip mushrooms in milk, then in flour, then in seasoned salt to batter them.
Place battered mushrooms in frying pan on medium heat in cooking oil.
Let cook until brown.
Drain and cool.
Serves 3.

title: copper pennies(marinated carrots)
directions: Combine and set aside vegetables.
Combine remaining ingredients and heat.
Pour over carrots and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: coconut-pecan chess pie
directions: Beat eggs well and add next 5 ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in coconut and pecans; pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: summer fruit and cheese mold
directions: Distribute the first box of jello into 3/4-cup boiling water. Stir in 3/4 cup of cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Put peaches on bottom of mold.
Spoon jello over fruit; refrigerate until set.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Grease 24 small muffin cups.
In a large bowl, sift together the dry ingredients.
Make a well in the center and add the buttermilk, eggs and butter.
Mix well.
Fold in the blueberries. Pour into muffin cups.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 muffins.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt margarine with brown sugar. Cool, then add egg and vanilla. Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt gradually. Spread in greased 9x13 pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: ranch salad dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ham rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread thinly on slice of ham. Form into rolls, then slice into bite size pieces.
You may use fancy toothpicks for serving.

title: crockpot sausage & kraut
directions: Brown sausage, carrots and onion. Combine all ingredients in crockpot. Cover and cook on medium heat for 4-6 hours.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix 2 eggs, cake mix and 1 stick melted butter, then press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant; drain and mash.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in small amount of oil or butter.
When eggplant is cool, add beaten eggs, onion, bell pepper, celery, tuna, shrimp and crabmeat.
Add seasoning.
Add bread crumbs to hold together (save some of the bread crumbs to spread on top).
Place in eggplant shell or casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs or Cheddar cheese or both.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
